1
00:00:32,379 --> 00:00:34,847
Dear Mr. Inman,

2
00:00:34,915 --> 00:00:37,782
I began by counting the days,

3
00:00:37,884 --> 00:00:39,852
then the months.

4
00:00:40,687 --> 00:00:45,818
I don't count on anything anymore
except the hope that you will return,

5
00:00:45,892 --> 00:00:51,592
and the silent fear that in the years
since we saw each other,

6
00:00:51,665 --> 00:00:58,229
this war, this awful war, will have
changed us both beyond all reckoning.

7
00:01:51,124 --> 00:01:53,592
This poor boy's from Alabama,

8
00:01:53,660 --> 00:01:57,426
- He's a long way from home,
- Thank you,

9
00:02:01,001 --> 00:02:03,993
why don't them Yanks just attack?

10
00:02:13,980 --> 00:02:15,845
Got any shirts, son?

11
00:02:22,522 --> 00:02:24,786
It's Mo Oakley's boy,

12
00:02:25,792 --> 00:02:28,727
Can't be old enough to fight, can he?

13
00:02:34,835 --> 00:02:37,360
- Good morning,
- Morning, son,

14
00:02:38,104 --> 00:02:40,698
Got some boots and jackets,
You want one?

15
00:02:40,774 --> 00:02:43,436
- Here, You want that?
- Thanks,

16
00:02:44,845 --> 00:02:47,336
I hope these boots can hold up
for 400 miles,

17
00:02:47,414 --> 00:02:50,406
'cause they're taking me
back to Cold Mountain,

18
00:02:55,422 --> 00:02:58,391
I think now
on the fleeting moments between us

19
00:02:58,458 --> 00:03:00,858
and wish I could repair them.

20
00:03:02,295 --> 00:03:06,425
My awkward nature,
the things left unsaid.

21
00:03:11,037 --> 00:03:13,528
All right, that's it,

22
00:03:17,878 --> 00:03:20,176
Enough powder here
to blow a hole in the sky,

23
00:03:20,247 --> 00:03:23,614
 Yeah,
a real Yankee good mornin',

24
00:03:38,098 --> 00:03:41,556
That old book of yours is in shreds,

25
00:03:42,736 --> 00:03:45,705
Same as us, Seen too much war,

26
00:03:47,240 --> 00:03:53,179
Hey, Oakley, Don't worry, son,
Them Yankee boys keep store hours,

27
00:03:53,246 --> 00:03:55,373
They ain't open yet,

28
00:04:05,025 --> 00:04:07,823
Close it up,

29
00:04:18,972 --> 00:04:22,738
- Hey, where'd you come from?
- Hey, that's fresh breakfast,

30
00:04:22,809 --> 00:04:24,800
- He's mine, Butcher,
- Hey! Hey! Get away!

31
00:04:24,878 --> 00:04:27,847
- Hey, I saw him first,
- Come on!

32
00:04:27,914 --> 00:04:31,475
- I saw it first!
- That's my rabbit! That's my rabbit!

33
00:04:34,387 --> 00:04:38,084
Get your paws off my rabbit!
Get your paws off my rabbit!

36
00:05:22,636 --> 00:05:25,230
when I came with my father
to the town of Cold Mountain,

37
00:05:25,305 --> 00:05:27,899
I was so shy of how I looked,

38
00:05:27,974 --> 00:05:30,534
so out of place.

39
00:05:30,610 --> 00:05:34,910
But did you know how happy I was
to escape from Charleston,

40
00:05:34,981 --> 00:05:38,849
from a world of slaves
and corsets and cotton?

41
00:05:38,952 --> 00:05:41,682
what do you fools think
you'll be fightin' for?

42
00:05:41,788 --> 00:05:45,224
- The South?
- I call this nail Northern Aggression,

43
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:48,522
-  Damn right,
- I call this nail the Yankee Skulls,

44
00:05:48,595 --> 00:05:51,325
last time I checked,
the South was a direction,

45
00:05:51,398 --> 00:05:53,923
Never figured you
for a lincoln lover, JT,

46
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:55,695
 I tell you,
as soon as I finish this chapel,

47
00:05:55,769 --> 00:05:57,896
I'm gonna go off
and kill me some Yankees,

48
00:05:57,971 --> 00:05:59,233
Piss and vinegar,

49
00:05:59,305 --> 00:06:01,796
Fightin' for a rich man's slave,
that's what,

50
00:06:01,875 --> 00:06:03,467
 whoa, here comes the minister,

51
00:06:03,543 --> 00:06:06,273
 Ben, thank you,
will you assist my daughter?

52
00:06:06,346 --> 00:06:08,314
lord have mercy,
look at that bonnet,

53
00:06:08,381 --> 00:06:10,212
look what's in it,

54
00:06:10,316 --> 00:06:12,284
 Oakley,
hand me the hammer, boy,

55
00:06:12,352 --> 00:06:14,252
That's a true Southern belle,

56
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:19,257
- Mr, Swanger! Good morning to you,
- Morning, Reverend,

57
00:06:19,325 --> 00:06:22,419
Esco, you remember my daughter, Ada,

58
00:06:22,495 --> 00:06:24,656
- Miss Monroe,
- Good morning,

59
00:06:24,731 --> 00:06:25,891
- Morning,
-  Morning,

60
00:06:25,965 --> 00:06:28,024
- Excellent progress,
- Morning,

61
00:06:28,101 --> 00:06:30,763
- Mrs, Swanger, Mrs, Castlereagh,
- Morning, Reverend,

62
00:06:30,837 --> 00:06:32,930
Now, if y'all will excuse me,

63
00:06:33,006 --> 00:06:37,943
In Charleston, my congregation would still
be disputing the size of the windows,

64
00:06:38,011 --> 00:06:38,773
 It's a chapel,

65
00:06:38,845 --> 00:06:41,871
Miss Monroe,
I was just thinkin' about you,

66
00:06:41,948 --> 00:06:45,748
Cold Mountain must feel
like the end of the world,

67
00:06:45,852 --> 00:06:48,412
Not at all,

68
00:06:48,521 --> 00:06:52,958
- It's very beautiful,
- well, you put us all to shame,

69
00:06:53,026 --> 00:06:56,189
Men up here had a bearing on
what they thought a woman was,

70
00:06:56,262 --> 00:06:59,561
- and then you showed up,
- Oh...

71
00:06:59,632 --> 00:07:01,896
- No, I doubt that,
- Oh, believe me,

72
00:07:01,968 --> 00:07:07,099
If you was to say a word to one of these
fools, I could get my top field cleared,

73
00:07:08,541 --> 00:07:10,873
- Any one?
- No, um...

74
00:07:11,811 --> 00:07:14,109
Him in particular,

75
00:07:14,180 --> 00:07:16,205
Up in the rafters,

76
00:07:16,282 --> 00:07:19,080
won't normally say boo to a goose,

77
00:07:22,088 --> 00:07:25,888
He's been pressin' me
since the day you arrived here,

78
00:07:29,929 --> 00:07:33,160
- Your top field cleared?
- That's right,

79
00:07:37,804 --> 00:07:41,331
Good morning, I'm Ada Monroe,

80
00:07:42,275 --> 00:07:43,833
Inman,

81
00:07:44,177 --> 00:07:45,371
Inman,

82
00:07:45,445 --> 00:07:47,310
wP Inman,

83
00:07:48,915 --> 00:07:50,382
wP Inman,

84
00:07:50,450 --> 00:07:53,180
Repeatin' a thing doesn't improve it,

85
00:07:55,088 --> 00:07:57,682
People call me Inman,

86
00:07:59,926 --> 00:08:01,791
How 'bout that? Inman speaks,

87
00:08:01,861 --> 00:08:05,888
If you were to take a glass of cider,
your friends might stop staring,

88
00:08:08,501 --> 00:08:10,469
Inman,

89
00:08:11,971 --> 00:08:16,999
 You're just jealous, I'm gonna
take her for a walk at Bishop's Creek,

90
00:08:17,076 --> 00:08:19,874
-  Billy, is this frame flush?
- Thank you,

91
00:08:19,946 --> 00:08:23,712
Yeah, yeah, yeah,
Thank you, yeah, right,

92
00:08:24,584 --> 00:08:27,747
 Richie, I seen your house, There
ain't a square angle anywhere near it,

93
00:08:27,854 --> 00:08:30,015
And what do you do?

94
00:08:30,123 --> 00:08:32,387
I work wood,

95
00:08:32,458 --> 00:08:34,289
Hunt,

96
00:08:35,328 --> 00:08:37,888
Mostly work wood,

97
00:08:40,099 --> 00:08:42,158
Clear fields?

98
00:08:46,339 --> 00:08:48,773
I can clear a field,

99
00:08:49,876 --> 00:08:53,642
was there something in particular
you wished to say to me?

100
00:08:58,218 --> 00:09:00,846
Not that comes to me,

101
00:09:07,193 --> 00:09:09,923
I'll say thank you... for the cider,

106
00:11:00,139 --> 00:11:02,903
Move back! Go back! Move back!

107
00:11:02,976 --> 00:11:05,672
Go back! Go back!

108
00:11:05,745 --> 00:11:10,580
They're trapped in the wrong
damn crater, whole plan backfired on 'em,

109
00:11:10,650 --> 00:11:12,948
 Send them Yanks straight to hell,

110
00:11:13,052 --> 00:11:16,044
-  Hold it, hold it,
-  let's go, Turn it around,

111
00:11:18,524 --> 00:11:21,322
 Damn fools
dug their own grave,

112
00:11:21,394 --> 00:11:24,022
 we've got 'em now, boys,

113
00:11:25,832 --> 00:11:29,495
- It's a turkey shoot,
- what?

114
00:11:29,569 --> 00:11:32,902
It's a turkey shoot,
They've run themselves into a hole,

115
00:11:32,972 --> 00:11:35,133
Hell's busted,

117
00:12:36,569 --> 00:12:38,628
Oakley!

118
00:12:50,683 --> 00:12:53,015
Oakley!

120
00:12:59,959 --> 00:13:01,722
Oakley!

123
00:13:28,087 --> 00:13:31,284
- Inman! Inman!
-  Oakley!

124
00:13:34,760 --> 00:13:36,455
Oakley!

127
00:14:04,290 --> 00:14:06,417
- Inman!
- Come on,

128
00:14:07,727 --> 00:14:09,558
Inman,

129
00:14:12,031 --> 00:14:14,465
- I've got you,

130
00:14:42,061 --> 00:14:44,689
I got a few,

131
00:14:44,764 --> 00:14:47,289
- You saw?
- I saw,

132
00:14:51,437 --> 00:14:54,099
Am I gonna die?

133
00:14:56,809 --> 00:14:59,471
Your folks can be real proud of you,

134
00:15:13,059 --> 00:15:17,894
 Son, this fellow says
he'll play whatever you want,

135
00:15:19,999 --> 00:15:23,799
what about Bonaparte's Retreat?
That's one I play,

136
00:15:28,975 --> 00:15:32,411
No, Play me somethin' sweet,

137
00:15:32,478 --> 00:15:35,345
like a girl's waiting for me,

138
00:15:36,315 --> 00:15:40,308
- You heard him,
- I only know a couple of tunes,

139
00:15:40,419 --> 00:15:42,887
like when you're at Bishop's Creek...

140
00:15:43,723 --> 00:15:46,658
and you're thirsty...

141
00:15:46,726 --> 00:15:49,627
and the water's so cool,

142
00:15:51,330 --> 00:15:53,525
I don't know what music that is,

144
00:16:18,924 --> 00:16:22,018
I'm reachin' Cold Mountain before you,

145
00:16:59,298 --> 00:17:01,198
 Good morning, Sally,

147
00:17:05,771 --> 00:17:09,229
- well, that's a fine-sounding thing,
- Oh...

148
00:17:10,042 --> 00:17:12,033
My piano,

149
00:17:13,646 --> 00:17:15,773
Oh, I've been missing it,

150
00:17:15,848 --> 00:17:20,581
Thank you, by the way,
Inman's in my top field clearing his debt,

151
00:17:20,686 --> 00:17:22,654
Oh, dear,

153
00:17:26,592 --> 00:17:28,924
And then he had nothing to say,

154
00:17:28,994 --> 00:17:31,485
He was happy,

155
00:17:32,765 --> 00:17:35,199
Really?

156
00:17:35,267 --> 00:17:38,134
Are men so different in Charleston?

157
00:17:40,206 --> 00:17:41,867
Men?

158
00:17:43,275 --> 00:17:45,266
I don't know,

159
00:17:45,344 --> 00:17:51,078
If you're sayin' you might like him,
why not go over and say good mornin'?

160
00:17:51,150 --> 00:17:53,141
I should be gettin' along,

161
00:17:53,252 --> 00:17:56,085
 walk on, quickly,

162
00:17:56,155 --> 00:17:59,249
Come on, walk on, Slowly,

163
00:17:59,358 --> 00:18:01,258
walk on,

165
00:18:45,671 --> 00:18:48,367
 My dear daughter, Ada,

166
00:18:48,441 --> 00:18:55,005
who's given up so much for so long to help
me in my ministry, and upon whom I rely,

167
00:18:57,616 --> 00:19:03,851
Friends, we are both very happy
to have this opportunity tonight...

168
00:19:04,990 --> 00:19:07,788
to thank you from our hearts...

169
00:19:08,928 --> 00:19:14,127
for your kind welcome
and, most of all, such a fine chapel,

171
00:19:15,634 --> 00:19:17,966
So... 

172
00:19:18,037 --> 00:19:21,029
... thank you, and God bless you,

173
00:19:24,143 --> 00:19:30,275
Our house is always open
to any of you at any time,

174
00:19:30,349 --> 00:19:32,840
welcome,

175
00:19:32,952 --> 00:19:33,976
Esco?

176
00:19:38,324 --> 00:19:40,292
That gentleman - he help build the chapel?

177
00:19:40,392 --> 00:19:43,384
 Him? No, that's Teague,

178
00:19:43,462 --> 00:19:47,364
At one time the Teague family
owned the whole of Cold Mountain,

179
00:19:47,433 --> 00:19:51,961
My farm, your farm,
it all belonged to his grandpappy,

180
00:19:52,037 --> 00:19:54,562
Teague wanted this place bad,
and you got it,

181
00:19:54,640 --> 00:19:57,438
And he's here sniffin' out an advantage,

182
00:19:59,512 --> 00:20:05,178
 There's no advantage here,
except to celebrate a job well done,

183
00:20:05,284 --> 00:20:07,377
And that is a good thing
in these troubled times,

184
00:20:07,486 --> 00:20:10,580
- Miss Monroe,
- Thank you,

185
00:20:15,394 --> 00:20:20,593
- were you never planning to come inside?
- I'm wetter than a fish,

186
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:24,932
- There's a good fire going,
- I'm all right,

188
00:20:27,673 --> 00:20:30,574
You're always carrying a tray,

189
00:20:32,811 --> 00:20:36,372
I was going to take some root beer
over to the Negroes,

190
00:20:44,523 --> 00:20:47,458
Somebody said you were enlisting,

191
00:20:47,526 --> 00:20:51,326
- Are you?
- If there is a war, we'll all fight,

192
00:21:04,910 --> 00:21:08,277
- Did you get a picture made?
- Say again?

193
00:21:08,347 --> 00:21:12,841
A tintype, with your musket
and your courage on display,

194
00:21:14,219 --> 00:21:16,710
You're laughin' at me,

195
00:21:18,257 --> 00:21:20,657
I don't know you,

196
00:21:24,430 --> 00:21:27,763
This doesn't come out right,

197
00:21:27,833 --> 00:21:33,362
If it were enough just to stand,
without the words...

198
00:21:35,140 --> 00:21:37,131
It is,

199
00:21:40,145 --> 00:21:42,045
It is,

200
00:21:45,751 --> 00:21:48,015
You... look,

201
00:21:48,120 --> 00:21:51,487
look, look at the sky now,
what color is it?

202
00:21:53,692 --> 00:21:56,559
Or the way... a hawk flies?

203
00:21:59,231 --> 00:22:02,029
Or you wake up...

204
00:22:02,101 --> 00:22:06,538
and your ribs are bruised
thinking so hard on somebody,

205
00:22:07,740 --> 00:22:10,231
what do you call that?

206
00:22:18,817 --> 00:22:20,785
I'll do that,

207
00:22:22,121 --> 00:22:24,851
I can't get much wetter,

208
00:22:27,393 --> 00:22:31,762
 what if you are killed,
and I'll never see you again?

209
00:22:31,830 --> 00:22:36,665
You said after a few years
I would barely remember your name.

210
00:22:36,735 --> 00:22:39,226
Oh, Inman.

211
00:22:39,304 --> 00:22:44,071
It is more than three years,
and I remember your name.

212
00:22:45,044 --> 00:22:47,842
Soldiers, Don't get up,

213
00:22:49,948 --> 00:22:52,075
You are mentioned tonight in my report,

214
00:22:52,184 --> 00:22:57,121
You men from Cold Mountain have
once again been heroes for the cause,

215
00:22:57,189 --> 00:23:00,989
There are Yankees in that stand of trees
between us, stuck there from the retreat,

216
00:23:01,060 --> 00:23:06,862
If they stay there, tomorrow mornin'
they can shoot us down for sport.

217
00:23:10,035 --> 00:23:12,026
Go around,

218
00:23:14,606 --> 00:23:16,369
-  It's a Reb!

219
00:23:16,442 --> 00:23:17,773
 How many of them are there?

220
00:23:17,843 --> 00:23:19,310
 I think there's five,

221
00:23:19,378 --> 00:23:22,279
 Under the trees,

222
00:23:24,349 --> 00:23:26,340
-  we got 'em,
-  let's go, let's go,

223
00:23:26,418 --> 00:23:28,978
 Butcher's down,

224
00:23:30,022 --> 00:23:34,220
 leave him, leave him,
He's gone, let's go,

225
00:23:35,627 --> 00:23:38,460
 Go, go! Go! Run!

226
00:23:39,698 --> 00:23:43,600
- Go! Go! Go!
-  Hold your fire!

227
00:23:43,669 --> 00:23:45,796
what's over by them trees?

228
00:23:45,871 --> 00:23:48,499
 It's us! It's us!

229
00:23:51,176 --> 00:23:54,111
I said hold your fire! Hold your fire,

231
00:24:00,319 --> 00:24:03,652
 leave him, leave him,

232
00:24:04,056 --> 00:24:05,819
Agh!

233
00:24:32,985 --> 00:24:35,385
Inman'll get it.

234
00:24:35,454 --> 00:24:40,255
Supposed to bring good luck,
a bird caught in a room,

235
00:24:40,325 --> 00:24:44,887
 I'm so sorry to have kept you
waiting, She'll just be a few seconds,

238
00:25:49,728 --> 00:25:51,821
- Mr, Inman,
- Reverend,

239
00:25:51,897 --> 00:25:54,730
- what can I do for you?
- I have some sheet music,

240
00:25:54,800 --> 00:25:58,258
It belonged to my father,
No use to me,

241
00:25:58,337 --> 00:26:00,032
Thank you,

242
00:26:00,105 --> 00:26:02,335
- You must come in,
- I should probably get along,

243
00:26:02,407 --> 00:26:05,672
Mr, Inman is more comfortable outdoors,

244
00:26:05,744 --> 00:26:09,510
Perhaps we might...
perhaps we might take a walk,

245
00:26:09,581 --> 00:26:11,572
A splendid idea,

246
00:26:14,419 --> 00:26:16,887
let me just get your hat,

247
00:26:20,525 --> 00:26:25,224
I dragged my poor daughter 400 miles
from Charleston to Cold Mountain

248
00:26:25,297 --> 00:26:29,666
because my doctors,
they've been sayin' my chest is weak,

249
00:26:29,735 --> 00:26:32,533
So the air's supposed to do me good,

250
00:26:33,538 --> 00:26:35,938
But it's the view I think heals,

251
00:26:36,008 --> 00:26:40,570
 It's what people say
we're fightin' for, To keep it that way,

252
00:26:40,646 --> 00:26:44,673
I have no plans to preach war
in my church, Mr, Inman,

253
00:26:46,184 --> 00:26:51,918
I imagine God is weary of being called
down on both sides of an argument,

254
00:26:54,092 --> 00:26:56,560
I imagine God is,

255
00:27:02,534 --> 00:27:04,525
Thank you,

256
00:27:06,138 --> 00:27:09,073
Now, your father played the piano, did he?

257
00:27:09,141 --> 00:27:11,336
That's right, He was a teacher,

258
00:27:11,410 --> 00:27:13,844
And is your father living, Mr, Inman?

259
00:27:13,912 --> 00:27:16,142
- He is not,
- And your mother?

260
00:27:16,214 --> 00:27:19,479
No, sir, She died when I was born,

261
00:28:16,308 --> 00:28:19,937
- Secession,
- North Carolina left the Union,

262
00:28:20,012 --> 00:28:26,042
for I don't care to stay here long

264
00:28:27,285 --> 00:28:29,753
- we got our war!
- whoo-hoo!

265
00:28:56,848 --> 00:29:01,444
we got our war! we got it!
we got it! It's about time,

266
00:29:01,553 --> 00:29:03,521
whoo!

267
00:29:05,657 --> 00:29:08,125
- All right!
- Inman! Inman!

268
00:29:08,193 --> 00:29:10,718
Ready to fight, son, ready to fight,

269
00:29:10,796 --> 00:29:11,888
whoo!

270
00:29:11,963 --> 00:29:14,363
we got our war, man,

271
00:29:14,433 --> 00:29:16,924
well, you have your war,

272
00:29:18,070 --> 00:29:19,264
Ada,

273
00:29:20,272 --> 00:29:22,103
Ada,

274
00:29:23,241 --> 00:29:26,210
It's a great day for North Carolina,

275
00:29:26,278 --> 00:29:30,305
Those who follow lincoln
or preach abolition...

276
00:29:31,316 --> 00:29:33,443
you best keep one eye open
when you're sleepin',

277
00:29:33,552 --> 00:29:36,715
OI' boogeyman might get you,

278
00:29:36,822 --> 00:29:40,121
Are you the law all of a sudden,
Mr, Teague?

279
00:29:40,192 --> 00:29:42,353
That's right, son,

280
00:29:42,427 --> 00:29:46,420
Home Guard for Haywood County,
