287
00:30:08,653 --> 00:30:12,851
- But then who'll be waiting for you?
- Three cheers for North Carolina!

288
00:30:12,924 --> 00:30:15,085
- All right,
- Three cheers for the South!

289
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,457
Hip hip hurrah!

290
00:30:16,795 --> 00:30:18,763
Hip hip hurrah!

291
00:30:19,097 --> 00:30:21,224
Hip hip hurrah!

292
00:30:32,911 --> 00:30:35,812
Inman, It belongs to Inman,

293
00:30:35,881 --> 00:30:38,213
I got it, He's here,

294
00:30:42,487 --> 00:30:47,686
They found that book
you been worryin' about, soldier,

295
00:31:27,132 --> 00:31:28,895
wait,

296
00:31:38,810 --> 00:31:42,678
I found you this book to take with you,

297
00:31:42,747 --> 00:31:44,908
william Bartram,

298
00:31:46,318 --> 00:31:48,786
They tell me it's good,

299
00:31:49,721 --> 00:31:53,919
I think he writes about these parts,
the author, so...

300
00:31:54,926 --> 00:31:56,917
Thank you,

301
00:31:58,463 --> 00:32:00,397
And this,

302
00:32:08,607 --> 00:32:11,167
I'm not smiling in it,

303
00:32:13,979 --> 00:32:16,777
I don't know how to do that,

304
00:32:16,848 --> 00:32:18,839
hold a smile,

306
00:32:42,440 --> 00:32:44,431
- Ada,
- what?

308
00:33:07,132 --> 00:33:09,623
- whoa!
- He'll be back in a month,

309
00:33:12,304 --> 00:33:14,636
Kiss her for me,

310
00:33:22,080 --> 00:33:24,139
Come on, let's go,

311
00:33:29,354 --> 00:33:32,255
I'll be waiting for you,

312
00:34:07,826 --> 00:34:09,293
lookin' good, Butcher,

313
00:34:09,361 --> 00:34:11,727
Bring home
some Yankee scalps, Swimmer,

314
00:34:11,796 --> 00:34:13,627
Yee-haw!

315
00:34:18,203 --> 00:34:23,368
look out the window, ladies.
See what these poor fools are dyin' for.

316
00:34:23,441 --> 00:34:27,639
How many would still lose a leg
for the rich man's slave?

317
00:34:28,446 --> 00:34:34,043
Most of these soldiers'll be dead by
morning, or if they're stubborn, by nightfall,

318
00:34:34,152 --> 00:34:38,748
I've other men outside
in the courtyard waitin' for beds,

319
00:34:38,857 --> 00:34:41,485
so any kind word will be a blessin',

321
00:34:44,996 --> 00:34:47,590
It's the heat, I'm sorry, They rot,

322
00:34:47,665 --> 00:34:50,190
Pigeon River...

323
00:34:50,268 --> 00:34:52,964
How are you, son?

324
00:34:53,037 --> 00:34:56,029
Cold... Mountain...

325
00:34:58,410 --> 00:35:00,742
I-I'm sorry,

326
00:35:00,812 --> 00:35:05,181
- You want water?
- Cold... Mountain,

327
00:35:07,051 --> 00:35:09,383
Cold Mountain?

328
00:35:10,054 --> 00:35:12,022
Cold Mountain,

329
00:35:15,427 --> 00:35:21,332
Do you worry when there's no word
from him? From Mr, Inman?

330
00:35:22,967 --> 00:35:24,798
Yes,

331
00:35:27,138 --> 00:35:29,800
But then I've tried countin'
the number of words

332
00:35:29,874 --> 00:35:34,811
which have passed between Mr, Inman
and me - not very many,

333
00:35:34,879 --> 00:35:39,111
But I think about him, Daddy, all the time,

334
00:35:39,217 --> 00:35:43,415
I lost your mother
after 22 months of marriage,

335
00:35:45,356 --> 00:35:47,824
It was enough to fill a life,

336
00:35:54,032 --> 00:35:56,159
 That was the last of the ham,

337
00:35:56,234 --> 00:35:59,635
-  It was delicious,
- I have to learn how to cook,

338
00:35:59,704 --> 00:36:02,070
I was thinking of saying
something in chapel,

339
00:36:02,140 --> 00:36:04,165
Perhaps some of the womenfolk
will volunteer,

340
00:36:04,242 --> 00:36:07,575
I can't have people coming here
and cooking for me,

341
00:36:09,447 --> 00:36:10,846
I so...

342
00:36:10,915 --> 00:36:12,507
I so regret...

343
00:36:12,617 --> 00:36:18,920
I should have raised you less like a
companion and more like a young woman,

344
00:36:18,990 --> 00:36:23,154
I'm sorry, Ada,
And for dragging you here,

345
00:36:23,228 --> 00:36:25,219
I'm not sorry,

346
00:36:28,433 --> 00:36:31,231
I would have followed you anywhere,

347
00:36:33,671 --> 00:36:36,333
- To Mongolia,
- Mongolia,

348
00:36:37,509 --> 00:36:42,776
But with no one left to work this place,
nothing to buy, nothing left to buy it with...

349
00:36:44,382 --> 00:36:48,341
I just don't know how we're gonna
get through another winter,

350
00:36:51,122 --> 00:36:56,890
will you play me somethin'? Somethin'
peaceful while I look over my sermon,

351
00:36:56,961 --> 00:36:59,088
It's too damp out here,
You should come inside,

352
00:36:59,163 --> 00:37:00,858
No,

353
00:37:00,932 --> 00:37:03,093
I like it,

354
00:37:17,749 --> 00:37:20,741
Daddy, bring the tablecloth in,

355
00:37:23,354 --> 00:37:25,822
Come inside before you drown,

359
00:38:13,571 --> 00:38:15,766
You have a letter,

360
00:38:15,840 --> 00:38:17,831
North Carolina,

361
00:38:19,577 --> 00:38:22,171
It's come a long way,

362
00:38:25,049 --> 00:38:27,381
It's not too recent,

363
00:38:27,485 --> 00:38:29,953
It's written this past winter,

364
00:38:32,256 --> 00:38:34,690
I'm afraid I can't read who it's from,

365
00:38:39,464 --> 00:38:41,898
Dear Mr, Inman...

366
00:38:42,634 --> 00:38:48,266
 Since you've left, time has been
measured out in bitter chapters.

367
00:38:48,339 --> 00:38:51,001
last fall, my poor father died.

368
00:38:52,944 --> 00:38:55,845
Our farm at Black Cove is abandoned.

369
00:38:58,750 --> 00:39:02,811
Every house in these mountains
touched by tragedy.

370
00:39:05,223 --> 00:39:10,092
Each day the dread...
of learning who has fallen...

371
00:39:11,295 --> 00:39:14,264
who will not return from this terrible war.

372
00:39:16,334 --> 00:39:19,303
And no word from you.

373
00:39:19,370 --> 00:39:21,497
Are you alive?

374
00:39:21,572 --> 00:39:24,370
I pray to God you are.

375
00:39:25,410 --> 00:39:27,776
This war is lost on the battlefield

376
00:39:27,845 --> 00:39:32,612
and is being lost twice over
by those who stayed behind.

377
00:39:32,717 --> 00:39:36,175
He ain't comin' back, you know that,

378
00:39:40,358 --> 00:39:42,952
You must know that in your heart,

379
00:39:45,663 --> 00:39:47,824
look at me,

380
00:39:49,467 --> 00:39:51,799
- look at me,

381
00:39:56,607 --> 00:39:59,235
I'm not nothin',

382
00:40:01,446 --> 00:40:05,849
 I'm still waiting,
as I promised I would.

383
00:40:08,619 --> 00:40:12,555
But I find myself alone
and at the end of my wits...

384
00:40:13,691 --> 00:40:18,355
too embarrassed to keep taking
from those who can least afford to give.

385
00:40:19,497 --> 00:40:22,466
Ada! It's Sally!

386
00:40:22,533 --> 00:40:23,761
Ada!

387
00:40:23,835 --> 00:40:26,099
look at the state of this place,

388
00:40:26,170 --> 00:40:29,731
- well, set it on the porch,

389
00:40:31,242 --> 00:40:34,769
She let them slaves go free,
and now...

390
00:40:34,846 --> 00:40:39,681
Poor soul, she's got nobody and nothin',
and waitin' on a ghost,

393
00:40:45,990 --> 00:40:47,981
Shoo!

395
00:40:50,595 --> 00:40:52,563
Go away,

397
00:40:57,568 --> 00:40:58,967
Devil!

398
00:41:02,473 --> 00:41:07,001
My last thread of courage now
is to put my faith in you...

399
00:41:09,447 --> 00:41:12,211
and to believe I will see you again.

400
00:41:13,417 --> 00:41:17,854
So now I say to you, plain as I can...

401
00:41:19,323 --> 00:41:22,588
if you are fighting, stop fighting.

402
00:41:23,828 --> 00:41:27,195
If you are marching, stop marching.

403
00:41:29,233 --> 00:41:31,724
Come back to me,

404
00:41:35,273 --> 00:41:37,605
Come back to me is my request,

405
00:41:45,750 --> 00:41:48,412
Come back to me.

406
00:41:49,921 --> 00:41:53,357
Come back to me is my request.

407
00:41:55,827 --> 00:41:59,786
wounded men, don't stray
from the hospital grounds,

408
00:42:00,364 --> 00:42:02,355
Hey!

409
00:42:04,235 --> 00:42:05,725
If they send us back to fight...

410
00:42:05,803 --> 00:42:09,739
Hey, get your peanuts now,
from the blind man,

411
00:42:11,175 --> 00:42:14,633
- Hey, your hot goobers here,
- It's a sad day,

412
00:42:18,583 --> 00:42:21,416
Gettin' better, soldier?

413
00:42:21,519 --> 00:42:24,215
Seems that way,

414
00:42:24,322 --> 00:42:26,290
I wouldn't hurry,

415
00:42:26,390 --> 00:42:30,417
The war's almost done,
Don't need your help to lose it,


417
00:42:31,629 --> 00:42:36,692
You got ten minutes now, boys, Ten
minutes to get your haircuts and shaves,

418
00:42:36,767 --> 00:42:39,634
I've been meanin' to ask you,
where'd you take your wound?

419
00:42:39,704 --> 00:42:42,070
Oh, before I was born,

420
00:42:42,139 --> 00:42:44,573
Never set eyes on a thing in this world,

421
00:42:44,642 --> 00:42:50,137
Not a tree, a gun or a woman,
Put my hand on all three, though,

423
00:42:51,916 --> 00:42:54,714
- what would you give for that?
- Hm?

424
00:42:54,819 --> 00:42:59,222
- To have your eyeballs for ten minutes,
- Ten minutes?

425
00:42:59,290 --> 00:43:01,815
I wouldn't give an Indian head cent,

426
00:43:01,893 --> 00:43:05,920
- Might turn me hateful,
- That's sure what seein's done to me,

427
00:43:05,997 --> 00:43:08,932
No, that's not the way I meant it,

428
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:11,560
You said ten minutes,

429
00:43:11,636 --> 00:43:16,073
It's havin' a thing and then
the loss of it I'm talking about,

430
00:43:16,140 --> 00:43:21,806
Then we don't agree, There's not much I
wouldn't give for ten minutes of someplace,

431
00:43:21,879 --> 00:43:25,975
Yeah, someplace... or someone,

432
00:43:29,053 --> 00:43:32,022
You watch yourself, now,

433
00:43:32,123 --> 00:43:35,115
They're shootin' men
who take themselves a walk,

435
00:44:13,965 --> 00:44:17,025
By order of Zebulon Vance,

436
00:44:17,101 --> 00:44:20,002
governor of this great state
of North Carolina,

437
00:44:20,638 --> 00:44:25,803
any soldier turned deserter
is guilty of treason,

438
00:44:25,876 --> 00:44:28,777
and should be hunted down like a dog,

439
00:44:30,147 --> 00:44:35,551
Any man who takes in a deserter
is likewise guilty of treason,

440
00:44:35,619 --> 00:44:41,956
The Home Guard is powered to enter any
place it sees fit without notice or constraint,

441
00:44:42,960 --> 00:44:45,929
Captain Teague needs more volunteers,

442
00:44:45,997 --> 00:44:50,195
Any man whose age or infirmity
prevents him from fightin' shall join us

443
00:44:50,267 --> 00:44:54,863
to protect this county from Yankee raiders
and traitors to the cause,

444
00:44:54,939 --> 00:44:56,736
- Is there a letter for me?
- Nothin',

445
00:44:56,807 --> 00:45:01,676
we've been gettin' no post through at all,
The sooner we lose this war the better,

446
00:45:01,746 --> 00:45:04,977
They say not one boy in ten
is comin' home to these mountains,

447
00:45:05,049 --> 00:45:10,180
Teague and his rabble throwin' their weight
around, They're worse than the Yankees,

448
00:45:10,287 --> 00:45:12,915
Might I speak with you, please?

449
00:45:14,525 --> 00:45:17,085
This was the Reverend Monroe's,

450
00:45:19,830 --> 00:45:22,628
I don't know who would want a watch,

451
00:45:24,802 --> 00:45:26,929
who can bear to look at the time?

452
00:45:30,341 --> 00:45:33,504
I've got a little salt pork you can have,

453
00:45:35,212 --> 00:45:37,612
Keep your daddy's watch,

454
00:45:39,283 --> 00:45:41,649
Thank you,

455
00:45:43,554 --> 00:45:45,351
I was talkin' to some of the other womenfolk

456
00:45:45,423 --> 00:45:48,187
about maybe lookin' in on you
at Black Cove, It's hard right now, but...

457
00:45:48,259 --> 00:45:52,127
Oh, no, I manage very well,
whatever the talk is,

458
00:45:54,498 --> 00:45:56,989
I'm very grateful for the pork,

459
00:45:59,370 --> 00:46:02,533
which I intend to pay for, of course,

460
00:46:11,115 --> 00:46:13,811
Is everything all right?

461
00:46:13,918 --> 00:46:15,715
Mm-hmm,

462
00:46:30,468 --> 00:46:32,265
 Ada,

463
00:46:32,336 --> 00:46:34,167
Ada,

464
00:46:36,107 --> 00:46:39,668
why, Ada, you are skinny
as a whippet, girl,

465
00:46:39,743 --> 00:46:43,201
- You are comin' indoors with me,
- No, I can't,

466
00:46:43,280 --> 00:46:45,271
I don't...

467
00:46:46,517 --> 00:46:48,610
I can't keep countin' on your kindness,

468
00:46:48,719 --> 00:46:50,744
Now, come on, I'm makin' a stew,

469
00:46:50,855 --> 00:46:55,758
we'd be proud to have you,
Esco's gonna be wantin' his dinner,

470
00:46:57,061 --> 00:47:00,497
I just wanna stop, I tell you, Yeah,

471
00:47:00,564 --> 00:47:05,001
Sit on the porch with Sal,
watch my boys in the fields,

472
00:47:05,069 --> 00:47:09,005
holler Good job every hour or so,

473
00:47:09,073 --> 00:47:12,839
That'll be a good day,
when our boys get home,

474
00:47:12,910 --> 00:47:15,970
what about your people in Charleston?

475
00:47:18,916 --> 00:47:21,680
There are no people,

476
00:47:21,785 --> 00:47:24,447
And there's no money,

477
00:47:24,555 --> 00:47:28,548
My father had some bonds
and investments,

478
00:47:28,659 --> 00:47:32,322
They're worthless now, of course,
The war...

479
00:47:33,898 --> 00:47:38,801
They're not worth anything,
I don't have anywhere else to go,

480
00:47:44,475 --> 00:47:46,739
I don't wanna go,

481
00:47:48,879 --> 00:47:51,939
- You're waiting on a feller,
-  Oh!

482
00:47:54,952 --> 00:47:57,011
- look down our well...
- Esco...

483
00:47:57,121 --> 00:47:59,089
She should,

484
00:47:59,890 --> 00:48:05,192
If you look down our well with a mirror,
you'll see the future, It's what they say,

485
00:48:06,730 --> 00:48:09,460
You do it,
She does it,

486
00:48:11,769 --> 00:48:13,464
what kind of mirror?

487
00:48:14,638 --> 00:48:18,369
- we'll hold on to you, Esco, you hold on,
- I got her,

488
00:48:18,442 --> 00:48:20,933
-  we got you,
-  Mm,

489
00:48:22,513 --> 00:48:24,504
See anything?

492
00:48:30,454 --> 00:48:33,423
-  I don't know,
-  I tried many a time,

493
00:48:33,524 --> 00:48:36,823
lookin' for a sign
my boys were comin' home,

494
00:48:36,894 --> 00:48:39,294
I never saw a dickey bird,

495
00:48:54,378 --> 00:48:57,279
- Oh!
-  Are you all right? Ada?

496
00:48:57,348 --> 00:49:00,283
what? what happened?

497
00:49:02,052 --> 00:49:04,714
what'd you see? what'd you see?

498
00:49:05,789 --> 00:49:09,122
Yesterday,
I saw you walkin' back to me...

499
00:49:09,927 --> 00:49:12,259
or thought I did.

500
00:49:13,197 --> 00:49:17,634
I found myself crouching
over Sally Swanger's well...

502
00:49:23,140 --> 00:49:26,507
...like a madwoman
staring into its secrets.

503
00:49:28,579 --> 00:49:34,142
was it you I saw walking home to me,
or was it your ghost?

504
00:49:34,251 --> 00:49:38,381
After so long, I know I must learn
to survive on my own

505
00:49:38,489 --> 00:49:41,617
and accept you will not return.

506
00:49:41,692 --> 00:49:45,093
And yet I cannot. I cannot.

509
00:49:50,734 --> 00:49:52,964
Them cows wants milkin',

510
00:49:53,037 --> 00:49:56,302
If that letter ain't urgent,
them cows is is what I'm sayin',

511
00:49:56,373 --> 00:49:58,398
I don't know you,

512
00:49:58,475 --> 00:50:01,672
Old lady Swanger says you need help,

513
00:50:01,745 --> 00:50:04,646
Here I am,

514
00:50:04,715 --> 00:50:09,652
I... I need help but... I need...
I do need help, but I need a laborer,

515
00:50:09,720 --> 00:50:14,714
There's... there's plowing and rough work,
I think there's been a misunderstanding,

516
00:50:14,825 --> 00:50:17,692
what's that rake for?

517
00:50:17,761 --> 00:50:20,525
- The rake?
- well, it ain't for gardenin', that's for sure,

518
00:50:20,597 --> 00:50:24,226
Number one, you got a horse?
I can plow all day, I'm a worker,

519
00:50:24,301 --> 00:50:26,735
Number two, ain't no man better'n me,

520
00:50:26,804 --> 00:50:31,070
'cause there ain't no man around
who ain't old or full of mischief,

521
00:50:32,476 --> 00:50:36,071
- I know your plight,
- My plight?

522
00:50:36,146 --> 00:50:39,673
Am I hard to hear?
'Cause you keep repeatin' everything,

523
00:50:39,783 --> 00:50:43,378
I ain't lookin' for money, I never cared for it
and now it ain't worth nothin',

524
00:50:43,487 --> 00:50:46,718
I expect to board and eat,
at the same table,

525
00:50:46,790 --> 00:50:49,953
- I ain't a servant, if you get my meanin',
- You're not a servant,

526
00:50:50,027 --> 00:50:54,726
People's gonna have to empty
their own night jars is my point,

527
00:50:54,798 --> 00:50:57,665
And I don't expect to work
whilst you sit around and watch, neither,

528
00:50:57,735 --> 00:50:58,861
Right,

529
00:50:58,936 --> 00:51:01,769
Right, Is that a yes or a no?

531
00:51:04,308 --> 00:51:07,368
There's a rooster,
He's the devil, I'm sure of it,

532
00:51:07,444 --> 00:51:10,004
I go near him
and he is at me with his spurs,

533
00:51:10,080 --> 00:51:12,275
He's lucifer himself,

534
00:51:12,349 --> 00:51:15,682
- I despise a floggin' rooster,

535
00:51:16,653 --> 00:51:18,621
Oh, no, I wouldn't...

536
00:51:18,722 --> 00:51:21,691
My name's Ruby Thewes,
