01:12:30,192 --> 01:12:32,251
- Get up,
- Evenin', Hank,

814
01:12:32,328 --> 01:12:33,989
Evenin', Hank,

815
01:12:34,664 --> 01:12:37,758
- You took your time,
- I said get up!

816
01:12:39,035 --> 01:12:43,028
Get in line,
You fools fall for it every time,

817
01:12:44,774 --> 01:12:47,902
 God will judge you, you Judas,

818
01:12:47,977 --> 01:12:51,378
- Thanks,
- God will judge you!

819
01:12:51,447 --> 01:12:56,111
- Move out!
- Our lives are on your rotten soul,

820
01:12:56,218 --> 01:12:58,015
- Mister?
- Your rotten soul!

821
01:12:58,120 --> 01:13:00,088
Shut your mouth!

822
01:13:01,991 --> 01:13:04,824
- Pleasure doin' business with you, boys,
- Judas!

823
01:13:04,894 --> 01:13:06,657
Save your breath,

824
01:13:06,729 --> 01:13:09,391
You got a long walk back to the fightin',

825
01:13:14,837 --> 01:13:17,931
Ada Monroe and Ruby Thewes,
look at you both,

826
01:13:18,007 --> 01:13:19,406
look at us both what?

827
01:13:19,475 --> 01:13:22,103
like a couple of scarecrows
after a thunderstorm,

828
01:13:22,178 --> 01:13:26,342
we need a scarecrow,
Birds done ate up half our winter garden,

829
01:13:26,415 --> 01:13:30,351
For all your kindness, coffee... and a pie,

830
01:13:30,419 --> 01:13:36,051
Yeah, and that's real coffee, It ain't chicory
and dirt, Found a sack hid in the larder,

831
01:13:36,125 --> 01:13:37,092
Mmm,

832
01:13:37,193 --> 01:13:38,956
Thank you both,

833
01:13:39,028 --> 01:13:42,964
Ruby, I look forward to this,
we all do,

834
01:13:43,032 --> 01:13:44,693
Esco and me,

835
01:13:45,468 --> 01:13:48,562
- She made it,
- I made it,

836
01:13:50,172 --> 01:13:52,436
Good God in heaven,

837
01:13:52,508 --> 01:13:55,306
I'm still livin',

838
01:13:55,377 --> 01:13:59,746
well, I know Esco's
gonna be real sorry he missed you,

839
01:14:11,293 --> 01:14:12,624
Yep,

840
01:14:17,266 --> 01:14:20,201
- Strike you as odd?
- what?

841
01:14:20,269 --> 01:14:24,729
- Stood at her front door,
- I know,

842
01:14:24,807 --> 01:14:28,937
Number one, I knowed that woman
all my life, I never stood outside her house,

843
01:14:29,011 --> 01:14:32,208
She'd let a wolf in if it knocked at the door,

844
01:14:32,281 --> 01:14:34,044
Perhaps...

845
01:14:34,116 --> 01:14:36,448
I don't know,
Perhaps she was busy,

846
01:14:36,552 --> 01:14:42,388
Number two, old man Swanger's inside
that house, I could smell his pipe burnin',

847
01:14:42,458 --> 01:14:47,054
- Number three, look at them fields,
- what about them?

848
01:14:47,129 --> 01:14:51,293
we come by here a week ago
and they was waist-high in hay,

849
01:14:51,367 --> 01:14:55,599
You tellin' me
that's work for one old man and his dog?

850
01:15:03,412 --> 01:15:05,505
Yankees! Yankees!

851
01:15:05,581 --> 01:15:08,311
Cavalry! Federal raiders!

852
01:15:08,417 --> 01:15:10,385
Just over that hill,

853
01:15:10,486 --> 01:15:13,455
- Get those sacks of shit up that hill,
- Come on!

855
01:15:21,063 --> 01:15:25,762
Get those horses under cover,
If they see us, we're dead,

856
01:15:26,368 --> 01:15:29,269
Make a move, make a noise...

858
01:16:03,005 --> 01:16:05,303
I'm gettin' out of this,

859
01:16:05,374 --> 01:16:09,777
I'm not gettin' shot again
for some cause I don't believe in,

860
01:16:09,845 --> 01:16:11,676
Come on, let's go,

861
01:16:11,747 --> 01:16:13,647
Come on, They can't shoot,
Come on,

862
01:16:17,953 --> 01:16:19,818
Keep goin'! Come on!

863
01:16:19,889 --> 01:16:22,619
Bayonets,

864
01:16:23,425 --> 01:16:25,290
Come on!

867
01:16:55,124 --> 01:16:59,618
Grab their boots
and rifles! let's move on!

868
01:16:59,695 --> 01:17:01,663
let's go!

869
01:17:17,146 --> 01:17:20,809
That scarecrow
ain't gonna frighten off no Yankee,

870
01:17:20,883 --> 01:17:23,818
Or are you tryin'
to make a man for yourself?

871
01:17:23,886 --> 01:17:25,376
No,

872
01:17:27,256 --> 01:17:31,352
I come by... a few days,

873
01:17:31,427 --> 01:17:33,918
- I don't pass by,

874
01:17:33,996 --> 01:17:37,227
- lookin' out for you,
- I know,

875
01:17:38,968 --> 01:17:41,061
I see you,

876
01:17:42,371 --> 01:17:45,636
- And I don't like it,
- where's your little servant girl?

877
01:17:45,708 --> 01:17:49,576
Ruby, She tradin' off
more of your daddy's silver?

878
01:17:49,645 --> 01:17:52,136
- Stop it!
- Her nose is in the butter,

879
01:17:52,214 --> 01:17:54,876
Her nose is right in your butter!

880
01:18:04,693 --> 01:18:07,161
This farm's got my name on it!

881
01:18:07,229 --> 01:18:10,892
You listenin', woman?
You're gonna need more than a scarecrow!

884
01:19:39,221 --> 01:19:41,189
Sal,

885
01:19:51,834 --> 01:19:53,825
Afternoon,

886
01:19:55,871 --> 01:19:58,533
Don't spread out,
why are they spreadin' out?

887
01:19:59,441 --> 01:20:02,205
I never seen a man work a field
with a shotgun before,

888
01:20:02,277 --> 01:20:03,676
There's a war on,

889
01:20:03,745 --> 01:20:05,804
Get off my land,

890
01:20:06,715 --> 01:20:10,048
- Your boys come home?
- Ain't seen my boys in four years,

891
01:20:10,152 --> 01:20:12,950
They're out fightin' other boys,
not old men and women,

892
01:20:13,021 --> 01:20:15,854
So you won't mind if we look around?

893
01:20:15,924 --> 01:20:18,188
'Cause we think they're here,

894
01:20:18,260 --> 01:20:20,956
we think you've got 'em
hid up somewhere,

895
01:20:21,029 --> 01:20:25,227
what I gotta give you?
Chicken? lamb?

896
01:20:26,602 --> 01:20:28,297
Sure,

897
01:20:28,370 --> 01:20:31,567
The thing is, you've only got one barrel,

898
01:20:31,640 --> 01:20:35,406
And there's five of us,
That's not a fair fight,

899
01:20:39,281 --> 01:20:41,215
King of kings!

900
01:20:42,217 --> 01:20:42,911
Hey!

901
01:20:44,853 --> 01:20:45,820
what was that?

902
01:20:47,289 --> 01:20:49,780
Aargh!

903
01:20:49,892 --> 01:20:53,828
You're harboring deserters, I could
confiscate this farm and everything on it,

904
01:20:53,896 --> 01:20:57,093
Every plate, every sheep,
every little pellet of chickenshit,

905
01:20:57,166 --> 01:20:59,430
I could confiscate your old lady's asshole,

906
01:20:59,501 --> 01:21:01,128
So don't you offer me no bird,

910
01:21:23,892 --> 01:21:26,759
Come on, boys!

911
01:21:26,828 --> 01:21:28,693
Mama's callin'!

914
01:21:36,905 --> 01:21:37,963
Mama!

915
01:21:38,040 --> 01:21:40,838
No!

916
01:21:40,909 --> 01:21:43,469
Mama! Mama!

917
01:21:45,080 --> 01:21:47,071
No!

922
01:22:24,386 --> 01:22:27,253
Buggery and shit!

923
01:22:27,322 --> 01:22:33,318
If I'da known you were this heavy,
I'da left you in those chains,

926
01:22:51,780 --> 01:22:53,771
Sally!

927
01:22:54,383 --> 01:22:56,112
No!

928
01:22:56,885 --> 01:22:59,046
No!

930
01:23:00,589 --> 01:23:02,056
Oh, God, Sally?

931
01:23:02,124 --> 01:23:03,421
Ada!

932
01:23:04,926 --> 01:23:06,917
All right, all right!

934
01:23:09,598 --> 01:23:11,691
Darlin', what?

935
01:23:12,868 --> 01:23:15,735
She's sayin' Don't bother! Go!

937
01:23:20,075 --> 01:23:22,100
Get her neck!

938
01:23:22,177 --> 01:23:24,805
- Sally!
- Get her neck,

939
01:23:28,483 --> 01:23:32,010
This world won't stand long,

940
01:23:32,387 --> 01:23:35,322
God won't let it...

941
01:23:35,390 --> 01:23:38,325
stand this way long,

942
01:23:43,565 --> 01:23:49,629
- How long have I been sleepin'?
- Two days, three days, Not long enough,

943
01:23:49,705 --> 01:23:53,664
- I can't stop here,
- Sit down before you fall down,

944
01:23:53,742 --> 01:23:56,370
I'm a deserter,

945
01:23:56,445 --> 01:23:59,778
If they find me here,
things could be bad for you,

946
01:23:59,848 --> 01:24:02,373
what are they gonna do?
Cut short my young life?

948
01:24:11,259 --> 01:24:14,956
I've learned a person
can pretty much survive off of a goat,

949
01:24:15,030 --> 01:24:17,863
A goat gives you company,

950
01:24:17,933 --> 01:24:19,730
and milk,

951
01:24:19,801 --> 01:24:21,632
and cheese,

952
01:24:21,703 --> 01:24:24,433
and, when you need it,

953
01:24:24,506 --> 01:24:26,303
good meat,

954
01:24:29,211 --> 01:24:31,202
That's my beauty,

955
01:24:31,480 --> 01:24:33,744
There's my beauty,

956
01:24:34,316 --> 01:24:36,910
So you been fightin',

957
01:24:39,688 --> 01:24:42,555
I could be at killin'...

958
01:24:42,624 --> 01:24:44,455
for days,

959
01:24:45,427 --> 01:24:48,885
my feet against the feet of my enemy,

960
01:24:49,931 --> 01:24:52,263
And I always killed him,

961
01:24:55,971 --> 01:24:57,836
He never killed me,

962
01:24:57,906 --> 01:24:59,897
I don't know why,

963
01:25:01,276 --> 01:25:04,336
Gave it a try, to look at ya,

964
01:25:06,148 --> 01:25:08,139
Yeah, I guess he did,

965
01:25:08,216 --> 01:25:10,013
See, I think there's a plan,

966
01:25:10,118 --> 01:25:12,643
There's a design
for each and every one of us,

967
01:25:12,754 --> 01:25:14,381
You look at nature,

968
01:25:14,489 --> 01:25:19,153
Bird flies somewhere, picks up a seed,
shits the seed out, plant grows,

969
01:25:19,227 --> 01:25:23,254
Bird's got a job,
shit's got a job, seed's got a job,

970
01:25:26,101 --> 01:25:29,229
And you've got a job,

971
01:25:29,304 --> 01:25:31,636
You done good, goat,

972
01:25:32,774 --> 01:25:35,106
You were a real beauty,

974
01:25:47,322 --> 01:25:51,156
Sometimes I think I'm crazy
when I'm just hungry,

975
01:25:51,226 --> 01:25:55,925
Now drink this,
It eases the pain, and you'll sleep,

976
01:26:03,071 --> 01:26:07,064
Is she waitin' for ya,
this Ada Monroe?

977
01:26:07,142 --> 01:26:09,337
She was,

978
01:26:09,411 --> 01:26:12,209
I don't know,

979
01:26:12,280 --> 01:26:15,613
Or even if she knows me,

980
01:26:15,717 --> 01:26:18,447
lie down,

981
01:26:18,553 --> 01:26:20,612
I'm like the boy
who goes for wood in winter

982
01:26:20,722 --> 01:26:23,885
and comes back in spring with a whistle,

983
01:26:25,126 --> 01:26:29,460
like every fool sent off to fight
with a flag and a lie,

984
01:26:32,300 --> 01:26:36,964
That's the laudanum gettin' to ya,
That's good,

985
01:26:37,038 --> 01:26:39,029
Say somethin' more,

987
01:26:43,812 --> 01:26:45,803
She got me a book,

988
01:26:47,215 --> 01:26:49,206
Ada Monroe,

989
01:26:51,653 --> 01:26:53,814
A man by the name of Bartram,

990
01:26:55,924 --> 01:26:58,119
He wrote about his travels,

991
01:26:59,194 --> 01:27:01,685
Sometimes...

992
01:27:01,763 --> 01:27:04,755
just readin' the name of a place...

993
01:27:05,934 --> 01:27:07,925
near home...

994
01:27:12,173 --> 01:27:14,164
Sorell Cove,

995
01:27:15,911 --> 01:27:17,902
Bishop's Creek,

996
01:27:19,481 --> 01:27:22,939
Those places
belonged to people before us,

997
01:27:24,219 --> 01:27:26,244
To the Cherokee,

998
01:27:26,354 --> 01:27:30,347
what did he call Cold Mountain?

999
01:27:32,827 --> 01:27:38,459
How could a name...
not even a real name...

1000
01:27:40,535 --> 01:27:42,867
break your heart?

1001
01:27:47,008 --> 01:27:48,999
It's her,

1002
01:27:51,046 --> 01:27:54,709
She's the place I'm headin',

1003
01:27:56,651 --> 01:28:00,553
And I hardly know her,
I hardly know her!

1004
01:28:04,626 --> 01:28:08,187
And I just can't seem to get back to her,

1005
01:28:12,867 --> 01:28:17,566
To have traveled so far,
from east to west,

1006
01:28:17,639 --> 01:28:19,903
a thousand terrible miles.

1007
01:28:19,975 --> 01:28:21,966
I have to close my eyes,

1008
01:28:22,043 --> 01:28:24,978
My feet treadin' all God's surface -

1009
01:28:25,046 --> 01:28:29,380
his ocean, his swamps,
his slopes and ridges -

1010
01:28:29,484 --> 01:28:35,423
to find myself, at last,
a mark in the aching snow,

1011
01:28:35,523 --> 01:28:38,185
from whence I beheld
through a blue haze

1012
01:28:38,259 --> 01:28:42,286
a world of mountains
piled upon mountains,

1013
01:28:43,231 --> 01:28:45,222
 Ada!

1014
01:28:46,635 --> 01:28:48,626
Ada!

1015
01:28:53,108 --> 01:28:55,167
- It's a man!
- what is?

1016
01:28:55,243 --> 01:28:59,805
Raidin' our corncrib!
Got him in the trap! That's him yelpin'!

1017
01:29:01,516 --> 01:29:04,246
- Help!
- Here,

1018
01:29:04,352 --> 01:29:07,014
Help! Damn,

1019
01:29:07,956 --> 01:29:10,049
listen up!

1020
01:29:10,158 --> 01:29:11,785
You got... Aim!

1021
01:29:11,860 --> 01:29:14,226
You got a barrel trained on your rear end!

1022
01:29:14,295 --> 01:29:17,355
- Get me outta this dang thing!
- You got a weapon?

1023
01:29:17,432 --> 01:29:22,426
No, ma'am, I'm...
My fists are about to drop off,

1024
01:29:22,504 --> 01:29:25,268
Unbelievable,

1025
01:29:26,141 --> 01:29:29,110
- Stobrod Thewes!
- Ruby?

1026
01:29:30,311 --> 01:29:32,779
Agh! 

1027
01:29:34,582 --> 01:29:36,914
That's my daddy,

1028
01:29:38,219 --> 01:29:41,347
Just so's you know,
I can eat while she's doin' this,

1029
01:29:41,456 --> 01:29:44,254
Just so's you know,
you ain't eatin' inside,

1030
01:29:44,325 --> 01:29:49,285
Number one, they hang people round here
for takin' in deserters,

1031
01:29:49,364 --> 01:29:53,425
Number two,
even if they was givin' out prizes,

1032
01:29:53,501 --> 01:29:56,129
you'd still eat outside,

1033
01:29:56,204 --> 01:29:58,502
- You're scarred,
- I'm what?

1034
01:29:58,573 --> 01:30:01,406
Your heart, Scarred,
I did wrong to ya,

1035
01:30:01,476 --> 01:30:05,708
You'd be scarred, You'd be real scarred if
I hadn't wrapped them trap teeth in sackin',

1036
01:30:05,780 --> 01:30:09,409
- which was my idea,
- which was her idea,

1037
01:30:10,452 --> 01:30:13,615
- I hurt you,
- Good God,

1038
01:30:13,722 --> 01:30:16,919
I made up 50 tunes with you in mind,

1039
01:30:16,991 --> 01:30:20,188
Ruby this, Ruby that,
Ruby with the eyes that sparkle,

1040
01:30:20,261 --> 01:30:23,025
Hey! let's agree,

1041
01:30:23,098 --> 01:30:27,296
You beat me,
you abandoned me, you ignored me,

1042
01:30:27,368 --> 01:30:29,029
then you beat me some more,

1043
01:30:29,104 --> 01:30:33,598
And all of that is better'n
Ruby with the eyes that sparkle,

1044
01:30:33,675 --> 01:30:36,473
I'm changed, People change,

1045
01:30:36,544 --> 01:30:38,603
war changes people somethin' terrible,

1046
01:30:38,680 --> 01:30:41,478
Ruby's told you, I've no doubt,
I wasn't always the best,

1047
01:30:41,549 --> 01:30:43,676
You were an asshole!

1048
01:30:43,785 --> 01:30:45,844
I can't disagree with that,
I was,

1049
01:30:46,521 --> 01:30:50,321
- would you get him outta here?
- Music's changed me,

1050
01:30:50,391 --> 01:30:52,382
I'm full of music, Ruby,

1051
01:30:52,494 --> 01:30:54,553
I wish I'd brung my fiddle,

1052
01:30:54,629 --> 01:30:56,927
Hey, Ruby, I got a new fiddle,

1053
01:30:56,998 --> 01:31:02,459
Oh, it's a beautiful fiddle, It's full of tunes,
Ruby, I didn't know I had it in me,

1054
01:31:02,537 --> 01:31:05,768
- You're all set,
- I...

1055
01:31:13,481 --> 01:31:16,143
Bless you both,

1056
01:31:18,853 --> 01:31:20,821
All right, then,

1057
01:31:26,094 --> 01:31:28,289
Ain't you got a proper coat?

1058
01:31:29,297 --> 01:31:33,859
Aw, darlin', I'm fine, you know, And you just
say the word, I won't come back neither,

1059
01:31:33,935 --> 01:31:36,699
Don't wanna put you or your mistress here
in any bother,

1060
01:31:36,771 --> 01:31:39,535
I'm not Ruby's employer,

1061
01:31:39,607 --> 01:31:41,541
Oh, Beg pardon,

1062
01:31:41,609 --> 01:31:43,440
Nobody is,

1063
01:31:43,511 --> 01:31:45,502
Oh,

1064
01:31:53,721 --> 01:31:57,623
You know who really needs a coat, darlin'?
My partner, Fat boy name of Pangle,

1065
01:31:57,692 --> 01:32:00,388
we're hidin' up in a cave
with a singer from Georgia,

1066
01:32:00,461 --> 01:32:05,421
and Pangle, he feels the cold like
a thin man, but there ain't no coat'll fit him,

1067
01:32:09,671 --> 01:32:11,070
I love you, Ruby,

1068
01:32:13,775 --> 01:32:17,336
In case the sky falls on our head,

1069
01:32:17,412 --> 01:32:19,937
You always were a good girl,

1070
01:32:30,225 --> 01:32:35,424
Ooh! He's so full of manure, that man,

1071
01:32:35,496 --> 01:32:39,432
we could lay him in the dirt and...
grow another one just like him,

1072
01:32:40,468 --> 01:32:43,369
That's medicine, that's goat meat,

1073
01:32:44,672 --> 01:32:46,867
And you're sick of both,

1074
01:32:46,941 --> 01:32:50,377
I have a deal to thank you for,

1075
01:32:50,445 --> 01:32:53,175
That's just for show,

1077
01:34:03,251 --> 01:34:05,742
- Get on back where you came from!

1078
01:34:05,853 --> 01:34:08,378
- Thank you for my coat!
- Thanks for the food!

1079
01:34:08,489 --> 01:34:11,549
- Git!

1080
01:34:11,659 --> 01:34:15,720
- I love my coat!

1081
01:34:27,976 --> 01:34:32,743
My love for linton
is like the foliage in the woods.

1082
01:34:32,814 --> 01:34:38,252
Time will change it, I'm well aware,
as winter changes the trees.

1083
01:34:38,319 --> 01:34:43,621
My love for Heathcliff
resembles the eternal rocks beneath.

1084
01:34:44,492 --> 01:34:47,655
A source of little visible delight,

1085
01:34:47,729 --> 01:34:49,890
but necessary,

1086
01:34:51,199 --> 01:34:53,599
He's always...

1087
01:34:54,769 --> 01:34:56,760
always in my mind,

1088
01:34:56,838 --> 01:34:59,136
She ain't gonna marry linton, is she?

1089
01:34:59,207 --> 01:35:03,337
You can't say that about Heathcliff
and then marry linton,

1091
01:35:04,946 --> 01:35:07,881
we'll find out,

1092
01:35:10,451 --> 01:35:12,681
Tomorrow,

1093
01:35:12,787 --> 01:35:16,223
I'm not waitin' till tomorrow!

1094
01:35:16,891 --> 01:35:18,722
Ruby...

1095
01:35:18,793 --> 01:35:23,321
A source of... little visible delight,

1096
01:35:24,499 --> 01:35:27,263
but... necessary,

1097
01:35:30,872 --> 01:35:34,000
I like that,

1102
01:36:00,768 --> 01:36:04,761
I'm a Confederate soldier...
on furlough,

1103
01:36:04,839 --> 01:36:07,933
I need shelter... and food,

1104
01:36:18,719 --> 01:36:21,051
I've got a rifle!

1105
01:36:21,956 --> 01:36:23,924
Fair enough,

1106
01:36:25,193 --> 01:36:27,593
I have some beans and corn pone,

1107
01:36:27,662 --> 01:36:29,823
All I got,

1108
01:36:36,938 --> 01:36:39,236
- Thank you,
- I'm alone here,

1109
01:36:39,307 --> 01:36:41,969
as you can see, with my baby,

1110
01:36:42,043 --> 01:36:44,739
I need to believe you mean no harm,

1111
01:36:48,416 --> 01:36:49,906
No,

1112
01:36:50,418 --> 01:36:52,613
I don't want it,

1113
01:36:52,720 --> 01:36:56,520
If I had my way, they'd take metal
altogether out of this world,

1114
01:36:56,591 --> 01:36:59,082
Every blade, every gun,

1117
01:37:13,774 --> 01:37:15,833
It's all right,

1118
01:37:15,910 --> 01:37:18,811
You're burnin' up, little man,

1121
01:37:35,163 --> 01:37:37,154
Is your baby sick?

1122
01:37:40,234 --> 01:37:45,604
My man's dead, Took his wound
at Gettysburg and never saw his boy,

1123
01:37:45,673 --> 01:37:46,833
I'm sorry,

1124
01:37:46,908 --> 01:37:50,867
It's pretty much what you'll get
if you knock on any door of this war,

1125
01:37:50,945 --> 01:37:53,743
Man dead, woman left,

1127
01:37:58,219 --> 01:37:59,948
It's mean food, but it's hot,

1128
01:38:00,054 --> 01:38:03,820
There's been no huntin' on the road,
just cress and roots,

1129
01:38:03,891 --> 01:38:06,951
I need to try and feed this man,

1130
01:38:07,028 --> 01:38:10,794
- Shh, You gotta eat somethin', baby,

1132
01:38:24,312 --> 01:38:26,940
He won't feed,

1133
01:38:27,014 --> 01:38:30,415
I'm Inman, by the way,
That's my name,

1134
01:38:31,986 --> 01:38:34,079
I'm Sara,

1135
01:38:36,891 --> 01:38:38,415
My baby's Ethan,

1136
01:38:39,994 --> 01:38:41,586
Glad to know you both,

1138
01:38:54,475 --> 01:38:57,672
You look about his size,

1139
01:38:57,745 --> 01:39:00,908
He was another man straight up and down,

1140
01:39:00,982 --> 01:39:03,041
Thank you,

1141
01:39:29,877 --> 01:39:31,674
Everything fit?

1142
01:39:33,281 --> 01:39:35,511
These boots are good boots,

1143
01:39:42,590 --> 01:39:45,252
well, I'll say good night, then,

1144
01:39:46,927 --> 01:39:48,918
Good night,

1146
01:40:12,753 --> 01:40:17,281
Christmastime will soon be over

1147
01:40:17,391 --> 01:40:22,055
then we'll join the band

1148
01:40:22,129 --> 01:40:24,996
- She don't speak?
- Can't speak! I told you,

1149
01:40:25,066 --> 01:40:27,296
well, is she feeble, then?

1150
01:40:27,368 --> 01:40:29,700
No!

1151
01:40:29,770 --> 01:40:31,101
Never mind him,

1152
01:40:53,994 --> 01:40:55,985
will you come inside?

1154
01:41:19,053 --> 01:41:25,424
would you do somethin' for me?
Do you... think you could...

1155
01:41:25,493 --> 01:41:30,294
lie here next to me and not...
need to go further?

1157
01:42:41,669 --> 01:42:45,605
- I'll go, I'll go, shall I?
- No,

1158
01:42:45,673 --> 01:42:48,005
I don't want you to,

1159
01:42:53,848 --> 01:42:55,839
Thing is...

1160
01:42:58,786 --> 01:43:01,050
I love someone,

1162
01:43:06,527 --> 01:43:09,155
I love someone very much,

1164
01:43:27,448 --> 01:43:29,439
Try and sleep,

1166
01:44:41,622 --> 01:44:51,463
Over home

1167
01:44:54,034 --> 01:44:57,470
- Merry Christmas, Pangle,
- Night, ma'am,

1168
01:44:57,538 --> 01:44:59,972
Merry Christmas, Georgia,
Nice to meet you,

1169
01:45:00,040 --> 01:45:03,339
- Merry Christmas, Miss Ada,
- Merry Christmas,

1170
01:45:03,978 --> 01:45:06,208
- Merry Christmas, darlin',
- Don't sleep here,

1171
01:45:06,280 --> 01:45:09,408
- we won't,
- It's dangerous, Don't sleep here,

1172
01:45:09,483 --> 01:45:13,476
Oh, it's bitter,
They could stop one night,

1173
01:45:13,587 --> 01:45:16,351
They stop one night,
they're gonna wanna stop two,

1174
01:45:16,423 --> 01:45:18,721
I'll be all right,
This coat's warm,

1175
01:45:18,792 --> 01:45:21,158
what about next Sunday?
lt'll be New Year,

1176
01:45:21,228 --> 01:45:24,925
- Maybe,
- Gonna be a better one than 1864,

1177
01:45:24,999 --> 01:45:28,992
- This war's over in a month,
- That's what he said a month ago,

1178
01:45:29,069 --> 01:45:31,537
It started off bein' over in a month,

1179
01:45:31,605 --> 01:45:34,335
Night, Miss Sally,
Merry Christmas,

1180
01:45:34,408 --> 01:45:37,468
-  Night, Miss Ruby,
- Night,

1181
01:45:38,412 --> 01:45:39,674
- Night, ma'am,
- Night,

1182
01:45:39,747 --> 01:45:42,238
You're stayin' with us tonight, Sally,

1183
01:45:42,316 --> 01:45:45,308
- That's my Ruby,
- She's an original,

1184
01:45:47,988 --> 01:45:53,517
- what kind of name's Georgia?
- It's where he's from, It's not his name,

1185
01:45:53,594 --> 01:45:58,896
well, I know it's meant to be
the ugliest state under the heavens,

1186
01:45:58,966 --> 01:46:01,696
why do you care what his name is?

1187
01:46:02,603 --> 01:46:05,868
Hey, what do you call
that cluster of stars right there?

1188
01:46:05,939 --> 01:46:08,066
Right there,

1189
01:46:08,142 --> 01:46:10,838
Uh... There? That's Orion,

1190
01:46:10,911 --> 01:46:16,144
And that's Gemini,
and that is Orion's big dog,

1191
01:46:16,216 --> 01:46:18,207
Canis Major,

1192
01:46:18,318 --> 01:46:20,445
listen to her, Sal,

1193
01:46:20,554 --> 01:46:23,887
She's turned into a regular highland girl,

1194
01:46:23,957 --> 01:46:29,554
Nah, I could always name the stars, Ruby,
That was never my problem,

1195
01:46:32,966 --> 01:46:35,799
I love you, darlin',

1196
01:46:35,869 --> 01:46:39,134
in case that big old sky falls on our heads,

1197
01:46:39,206 --> 01:46:40,468
Aw...

1198
01:46:43,744 --> 01:46:47,373
And I love you too, Sally,
I do,

1199
01:46:50,317 --> 01:46:52,785
- Get up!

1200
01:46:52,853 --> 01:46:56,345
Get up! Get out of here, quick!
The Yankees are coming!

1201
01:46:56,457 --> 01:46:58,288
The Yankees, they're here,

1202
01:46:58,358 --> 01:47:02,294
If they find you here,
things'll go bad on all of us,

1203
01:47:02,362 --> 01:47:05,991
- I can try and fight 'em,
- No, My baby, Please, no, Just...

1204
01:47:06,066 --> 01:47:08,057
Please, just git!

1205
01:47:20,080 --> 01:47:23,811
we're Union army!
we're lookin' for food!

1206
01:47:23,917 --> 01:47:26,477

Come on, open up! we're hungry!

1207
01:47:26,587 --> 01:47:29,181
- I got nothin'! I got nothin'!
- we'll see about that,

1209
01:47:31,658 --> 01:47:35,492
- There's a baby inside, Get it,
- Please, he's sick, Don't hurt him, please,

1210
01:47:35,562 --> 01:47:37,530
Please, I got nothin'!

1212
01:47:40,267 --> 01:47:43,794
That's right, Take the chickens,
Take the chickens, They're all I got,

1213
01:47:47,841 --> 01:47:49,934
Says she's only got chickens,

1214
01:47:50,010 --> 01:47:53,571
- You lyin' Southern trash,

1215
01:47:54,248 --> 01:47:56,239
we're hungry,

1216
01:47:56,316 --> 01:47:57,806
we got all day,

1217
01:47:58,786 --> 01:48:01,653
See, those birds
won't get you through the winter,

1218
01:48:01,722 --> 01:48:03,485
Please cover up my boy,

1219
01:48:03,557 --> 01:48:06,287
Just tell us where the food is,
we'll pick him up,

1220
01:48:06,360 --> 01:48:08,851
- Please, my baby's sick,

1221
01:48:08,929 --> 01:48:11,022
Please, just cover him up,

1222
01:48:11,098 --> 01:48:14,625
Please, I'm beggin' you!

1223
01:48:14,701 --> 01:48:17,397
Please! Have mercy!

1224
01:48:19,540 --> 01:48:22,338
- I got a hog!

1225
01:48:22,409 --> 01:48:23,808
I got a hog!

1226
01:48:23,877 --> 01:48:27,438
- He's hid out behind the house!
- Take a look,

1227
01:48:28,649 --> 01:48:31,482
Please! 

1228
01:48:33,053 --> 01:48:35,715
Please, sir, Please,

1229
01:48:35,823 --> 01:48:37,814
He's just a baby!

1230
01:48:39,560 --> 01:48:42,028
- He's shaking!

1231
01:48:42,095 --> 01:48:44,825
Please, just cover him up,

1232
01:48:44,898 --> 01:48:49,335
what's wrong with you?
what's wrong with you?

1234
01:48:50,938 --> 01:48:53,930
I ain't got nothin' else, I swear,

1235
01:48:54,007 --> 01:48:56,942
- That ain't necessarily so,
- Yes,

1236
01:48:57,010 --> 01:48:59,774
Take me inside,
we'll do whatever you want,

1237
01:48:59,847 --> 01:49:04,511
Take my baby inside,
let's all go inside! Please!

1238
01:49:04,618 --> 01:49:07,519
Please! Please!

1239
01:49:07,588 --> 01:49:10,751
You take that hog!
I'm as good as dead!

1240
01:49:10,824 --> 01:49:13,918
Take that hog 'cause I'm as good as dead!

1241
01:49:14,094 --> 01:49:16,358
- Shut up!

1242
01:49:21,368 --> 01:49:23,734
No! Agh!

1245
01:49:30,110 --> 01:49:33,511
- You know, he's gettin' ready to take a fit,
- what do you care?

1248
01:49:48,028 --> 01:49:50,588
- Shh... Shh...

1249
01:49:50,664 --> 01:49:53,132
That's better, Shh, That's better,

1250
01:49:56,803 --> 01:49:59,636
Hey, come on,
leave some for the rest of us,

1252
01:50:10,417 --> 01:50:12,885
Move away from the baby!

1253
01:50:14,588 --> 01:50:16,715
Towards me!

1254
01:50:16,823 --> 01:50:20,281
Don't shoot,
we just wanted food,

1255
01:50:20,394 --> 01:50:22,726
Take off your boots,

1256
01:50:24,364 --> 01:50:27,731
Take off your pants,
Take off your shirt,

1258
01:50:35,108 --> 01:50:37,099
Don't shoot me, please,

1259
01:50:38,645 --> 01:50:41,978
we're starvin',
we haven't eaten in days,

1260
01:50:42,049 --> 01:50:46,748
- Come on,
- we're starving, we haven't eaten in days,

1261
01:50:46,853 --> 01:50:48,878
Come on!

1262
01:50:51,658 --> 01:50:54,252
Thanks, Thank you,

1263
01:50:54,328 --> 01:50:56,592
- Now you get runnin',
- I will,

1264
01:50:56,663 --> 01:50:58,961
- And keep runnin',
- Thank you,

1267
01:51:59,393 --> 01:52:03,989
- I love the snow,
- I hate the snow, I hate the cold,

1268
01:52:05,932 --> 01:52:08,924
- Come on!
- Fellas, what's the rush?

1269
01:52:09,002 --> 01:52:13,564
If Ruby finds out we've spent the night,
there'll be hell to pay,

1270
01:52:50,210 --> 01:52:53,373
 My love, where are you?

1271
01:52:54,281 --> 01:52:57,876
with no hope of reaching you,
I write to you,

1272
01:52:57,984 --> 01:52:59,952
as I always do,

1273
01:53:01,922 --> 01:53:04,254
as I have always done.

1275
01:53:24,711 --> 01:53:27,839
You reckon we could eat this?

1276
01:53:28,548 --> 01:53:30,175
Hey,

1277
01:53:30,250 --> 01:53:33,913
well, you know, you cook somethin'
long enough, you can eat anything,

1278
01:53:34,020 --> 01:53:37,251
It's froze,
How long it been there for?

1279
01:53:37,324 --> 01:53:40,225
- You hungry?
- Yeah,

1280
01:53:40,293 --> 01:53:42,386
Not very long,

1285
01:54:19,099 --> 01:54:20,999
Good evenin',

1286
01:54:21,067 --> 01:54:23,763
Hope we didn't disturb you,

1287
01:54:23,837 --> 01:54:28,069
D'you mind if I warm myself by your fire?

1288
01:54:28,808 --> 01:54:30,537
Name's Teague,

1289
01:54:30,610 --> 01:54:33,204
- Do I know you?
- Stobrod Thewes,

1290
01:54:33,280 --> 01:54:34,269


1291
01:54:34,414 --> 01:54:36,644
- That your wife?
- That's a he,

1292
01:54:36,716 --> 01:54:38,479
Is he your wife?

1293
01:54:38,585 --> 01:54:43,147
we're musicians,
He picks a banjo, I got a fiddle,

1294
01:54:43,256 --> 01:54:46,589
Your sweetheart's got
a nice piece of flesh on him,

1295
01:54:46,660 --> 01:54:50,118
- He looks pretty romantic by the fire,
- It's a picture of love,

1297
01:54:56,770 --> 01:54:59,102
You gonna play that fiddle?

1298
01:54:59,172 --> 01:55:00,605
Sure,

1299
01:55:00,874 --> 01:55:02,739
Sure,

1300
01:55:02,809 --> 01:55:04,800
Hey, wake up,

1301
01:55:06,479 --> 01:55:08,470
Evenin', missis,

1302
01:55:09,216 --> 01:55:11,946
- where's Georgia?
- where's Georgia?

1304
01:55:16,256 --> 01:55:19,748
- Captain Teague wants us to play now,
- love to,

1305
01:55:19,859 --> 01:55:23,625
we heard there were some deserters
up in these parts hidden out in a big cave,

1306
01:55:23,697 --> 01:55:26,632
- Not come to my ears,
- So you don't know where this big cave is?

1307
01:55:26,700 --> 01:55:28,634
- No, sir,
- You do, Stobs, He means...

1308
01:55:28,702 --> 01:55:30,226
No, right, No, no,

1309
01:55:30,303 --> 01:55:34,069
There is a cave right up near Bearpen
Branch, we played some music up there,

1310
01:55:34,140 --> 01:55:38,668
- Never occurred to me they were outliers,
- It ain't nowhere near Bearpen Branch,

1311
01:55:38,745 --> 01:55:40,576
He's always gettin' lost,

1312
01:55:40,647 --> 01:55:43,548
That cave - we live there,

1313
01:55:43,650 --> 01:55:48,053
I used to freeze up in that cave
till I got gived this new coat,

1314
01:55:48,121 --> 01:55:52,148
Ruby made me this coat,
I like my coat,

1315
01:55:52,259 --> 01:55:55,626
This part belonged to a reverend
and this part belonged to a horse,

1316
01:55:55,695 --> 01:56:00,359
Ruby said - what is it? - 
I should pray or neigh, dependin',

1317
01:56:00,433 --> 01:56:02,697
He don't...
he don't know what he's sayin',

1318
01:56:02,769 --> 01:56:06,603
He got a mind
no bigger than a pickled walnut,

1319
01:56:06,673 --> 01:56:09,642
- It's a good coat,

1320
01:56:54,554 --> 01:57:02,086
On a sour apple tree

1321
01:57:46,206 --> 01:57:48,071
Broke my young heart,

1323
01:57:52,612 --> 01:57:54,603
we gonna be here all night?

1324
01:57:57,150 --> 01:57:59,141
Stand over there,

1325
01:58:10,296 --> 01:58:13,925
Ruby, she don't know
one end of the war from the other,

1326
01:58:14,000 --> 01:58:17,094
You don't have to worry yourself about her,
is what I'm sayin',

1327
01:58:17,170 --> 01:58:21,038
Or Ada, neither,
You know what I'm sayin'?

1328
01:58:21,107 --> 01:58:23,837
You too,
You stand over there,

1329
01:58:26,846 --> 01:58:29,246
we gonna get our tintype made?

1330
01:58:35,889 --> 01:58:37,720
Don't smile,

1331
01:58:37,791 --> 01:58:39,520
- what?
- Quit smilin',

1332
01:58:39,592 --> 01:58:41,890
He always smiles,
He don't mean nothin' by it,

1333
01:58:41,961 --> 01:58:44,623
I told him, there ain't nothin' in this world
worth a smile!

1334
01:58:44,697 --> 01:58:47,222
Put your hat over your face,

1335
01:58:54,007 --> 01:58:56,032
Cover your face with your hat,

1336
01:59:04,751 --> 01:59:06,685
-  Ruby!
- what?

1337
01:59:07,320 --> 01:59:08,947
- Ruby!
- what's wrong?

1338
01:59:09,055 --> 01:59:12,491
- Teague... The Home Guard...
- what?

1339
01:59:13,560 --> 01:59:15,653
They shot your daddy!

1340
01:59:15,728 --> 01:59:17,821
They shot your daddy, and Pangle too!

1341
01:59:23,870 --> 01:59:28,102
I told Georgia he can stop here,
I told him he can sleep in the barn,

1342
01:59:28,174 --> 01:59:32,042
He's got nothin' inside him,
He'll walk out of here and die in the snow,

1343
01:59:32,111 --> 01:59:35,342
He can milk the cows,
I was worried about that,

1344
01:59:37,684 --> 01:59:41,620
It's five hours' climb from here,
He drew a map,

1345
01:59:41,721 --> 01:59:43,689
I'm ready,

1346
01:59:44,591 --> 01:59:47,424
You know them fools
stayed the night in the mill?

1347
01:59:48,695 --> 01:59:52,791
That's Stobrod Thewes, Can't do
one good thing without addin' the bad,

1348
01:59:52,866 --> 01:59:57,360
left tracks in the snow all the way up
for the Home Guard to follow,

1349
01:59:57,437 --> 01:59:59,735
- Sign that says Shoot me,
- Ruby...

1350
02:00:03,076 --> 02:00:04,566
Ruby,

1351
02:00:06,779 --> 02:00:08,940
I'm sorry,

1352
02:00:10,950 --> 02:00:13,851
Every piece of this is man's bullshit,

1353
02:00:13,920 --> 02:00:16,548
They call this war a cloud over the land,

1354
02:00:16,656 --> 02:00:21,423
but they made the weather, and then they
stand in the rain and say Shit, it's rainin'!

1355
02:00:27,100 --> 02:00:32,333
If I cry one tear for my daddy,
I stole it off a crocodile,

1356
02:00:36,142 --> 02:00:37,200
All right, then,

1357
02:01:26,659 --> 02:01:28,650
All right, then,

1358
02:01:29,696 --> 02:01:32,688
Dear God,

1359
02:01:37,003 --> 02:01:38,994
Oh, dear God,

1360
02:01:45,445 --> 02:01:47,913
He ain't here,

1361
02:01:47,981 --> 02:01:51,974
Agh! Teague's probably took him,

1362
02:01:52,085 --> 02:01:55,919
They did that with the Swanger boys,
didn't they?

1363
02:01:55,989 --> 02:01:58,958
Strung 'em up, as a warnin',

1364
02:02:04,197 --> 02:02:06,461
They took his coat,

1365
02:02:06,532 --> 02:02:08,397
why would they take his coat?

1367
02:02:14,273 --> 02:02:16,741
Daddy? Daddy!

1368
02:02:17,176 --> 02:02:19,167
Daddy!

1369
02:02:25,151 --> 02:02:26,846
- Daddy?

1370
02:02:26,953 --> 02:02:29,353
He's still breathin'!

1371
02:02:29,422 --> 02:02:31,822
It's Ruby!

1372
02:02:31,891 --> 02:02:33,620
Don't you die on me again!

1373
02:02:40,166 --> 02:02:43,966
- we gotta get him home,
- He won't make it, He'll die first,

1374
02:02:44,037 --> 02:02:47,438
He's got hardly no blood left in him,

1375
02:02:50,209 --> 02:02:52,200
 There it is, I feel it,

1376
02:02:52,278 --> 02:02:53,302
- You got it?
- Yep,

1377
02:02:54,280 --> 02:02:58,808
 There's a place close.
Old Cherokee, it used to be.

1378
02:02:58,918 --> 02:03:01,148
It's got shelter, water.

1379
02:03:01,254 --> 02:03:03,916
I used to hide up there
when he'd get a temper goin'.

1380
02:03:04,023 --> 02:03:05,991
God!

1381
02:03:13,399 --> 02:03:17,392
- I'll go look for some food,
- Take the shotgun,

1382
02:03:43,362 --> 02:03:45,057
Goddamn,

1384
02:03:55,875 --> 02:03:57,866
Turn around!

1385
02:03:59,445 --> 02:04:02,005
Go back where you came from!

1386
02:04:03,616 --> 02:04:05,106
Go back!

1387
02:04:09,422 --> 02:04:11,481
Ada?

1388
02:04:12,125 --> 02:04:13,285
Ada Monroe?

1389
02:04:15,394 --> 02:04:18,192
Turn around or I'll shoot!

1390
02:04:46,759 --> 02:04:48,090
Inman?

1391
02:04:48,427 --> 02:04:50,418
Inman?

1392
02:05:03,476 --> 02:05:05,637
Inman,

1393
02:05:37,877 --> 02:05:39,970
You better come with me,

1394
02:05:52,625 --> 02:05:54,593
Ruby,

1395
02:05:55,494 --> 02:05:57,121
This is Inman,

1396
02:06:02,201 --> 02:06:04,635
Oh! Congratulations!

1397
02:06:04,704 --> 02:06:08,231
Oughta send you out with a shotgun
a lot more!

1398
02:06:09,976 --> 02:06:12,035
looks if he's about to topple over,

1399
02:06:13,279 --> 02:06:15,873
- I may need to,
- You shot or somethin'?

1400
02:06:17,884 --> 02:06:19,442
Not lately,

1401
02:06:30,830 --> 02:06:33,924
- He's asleep,
- I ain't surprised,

1402
02:06:34,000 --> 02:06:38,437
- Your man looked tuckered out,
- I saw him,

1403
02:06:38,504 --> 02:06:42,770
In Sally Swanger's well,
A man like a black smudge in the snow,

1404
02:06:42,842 --> 02:06:46,278
- well, there you go,
- It wasn't the same, what I saw,

1405
02:06:46,345 --> 02:06:48,506
In the well it was as if he were falling,

1406
02:06:48,581 --> 02:06:52,108
- You probably just don't remember it right,
- I remember it exactly,

1407
02:06:52,218 --> 02:06:54,277
There were crows - black crows,

1408
02:06:54,387 --> 02:06:56,514
They were flyin' towards me,

1409
02:06:56,622 --> 02:06:59,921
Ruby, I thought I was seein' him fall,

1410
02:07:02,261 --> 02:07:05,321
Instead, I was seein' him come back to me,

1411
02:07:07,700 --> 02:07:11,158
I got big plans for that farm,

1412
02:07:15,174 --> 02:07:17,005
I know,

1413
02:07:17,977 --> 02:07:19,774
I know you have,

1414
02:07:19,845 --> 02:07:23,781
I got a vision in my mind
of how Black Cove oughta be,

1415
02:07:27,853 --> 02:07:30,253
I don't know, Ruby,

1416
02:07:30,323 --> 02:07:34,555
All this while
I've been packin' ice around my heart,

1417
02:07:37,196 --> 02:07:39,994
How do I make it melt?

1418
02:07:42,935 --> 02:07:44,402
 Hey!

1419
02:07:45,338 --> 02:07:47,772
You about done with my knife?

1420
02:07:48,441 --> 02:07:50,671
we got a bird to cook,

1421
02:07:51,177 --> 02:07:53,008
 Just about,

1422
02:07:55,815 --> 02:07:59,649
You're makin' a pig's ear of that job,

1423
02:08:01,120 --> 02:08:03,088
Give it to me,

1424
02:08:09,061 --> 02:08:11,689
Oh, I ain't gonna cut you,

1425
02:08:13,499 --> 02:08:17,731
Can't see that it'd make
a bit of difference if I did,

1426
02:08:28,481 --> 02:08:30,779
You got the right feelings for her?

1427
02:08:31,217 --> 02:08:34,118
Don't turn your head! Tsk,

1428
02:08:37,823 --> 02:08:39,222
I do,

1430
02:09:04,850 --> 02:09:07,944
I'm sorry,
I was tryin' to be quiet,

1431
02:09:13,959 --> 02:09:16,291
Did you get my letters?

1432
02:09:18,030 --> 02:09:20,021
I got three letters,

1433
02:09:21,033 --> 02:09:25,561
I carried them,
I carried them in the book you gave me,

1434
02:09:25,638 --> 02:09:27,299
The Bartram,

1435
02:09:28,407 --> 02:09:31,843
I probably sent 103,

1436
02:09:36,582 --> 02:09:39,244
Did you write to me?

1437
02:09:39,351 --> 02:09:41,148
whenever I could,

1438
02:09:41,253 --> 02:09:43,517
If you never got them, I can summarize,

1439
02:09:43,589 --> 02:09:46,422
- No, No, no,
- I pray you are well,

1440
02:09:46,492 --> 02:09:48,824
I pray I am in your thoughts,

1441
02:09:48,894 --> 02:09:54,161
You are all that keeps me
from slidin' into some dark place,

1442
02:09:54,233 --> 02:09:57,361
How did I keep you?

1443
02:09:57,436 --> 02:10:00,303
we barely knew each other,
It was a few moments,

1444
02:10:00,372 --> 02:10:02,237
A thousand moments,

1445
02:10:05,144 --> 02:10:08,773
They're like a bag...
of tiny diamonds,

1446
02:10:10,282 --> 02:10:14,150
Don't matter if they're real
or things I made up,

1447
02:10:16,088 --> 02:10:18,147
The shape of your neck,

1448
02:10:20,159 --> 02:10:22,150
That's real,

1449
02:10:22,761 --> 02:10:26,720
The way you felt under my hands
when I pulled you to me,

1450
02:10:38,043 --> 02:10:40,671
You were plowing a field,

1451
02:10:41,680 --> 02:10:44,308
You were carrying a tray,

1452
02:10:44,383 --> 02:10:47,113
- You wouldn't come in,
- No, I wouldn't go in,

1453
02:10:47,219 --> 02:10:52,122
So that's why I had to carry a tray,
So I could come out to see you,

1454
02:10:54,193 --> 02:10:57,287
That kiss,

1455
02:10:57,363 --> 02:11:00,924
which I kissed every day of my walking,

1456
02:11:02,668 --> 02:11:04,761
Every day I was waiting,

1457
02:11:05,571 --> 02:11:07,095
longing,

1458
02:11:07,173 --> 02:11:10,233
longing to see your face,

1459
02:11:16,415 --> 02:11:19,748
If you could see my inside...

1460
02:11:19,852 --> 02:11:24,789
Now, whatever you wanna name it -
my spirit? That's what I fear,

1461
02:11:25,891 --> 02:11:27,859
I think I'm ruined,

1462
02:11:27,927 --> 02:11:31,693
They kept tryin' to put me in the ground,

1463
02:11:32,698 --> 02:11:35,360
- But I wasn't ready,
- Inman...

1464
02:11:35,434 --> 02:11:38,835
But if I had... if I had goodness,
I lost it,

1465
02:11:41,106 --> 02:11:44,303
If I had anything tender in me,
I shot it dead,

1466
02:11:46,045 --> 02:11:49,845
How could I write to you after what I done,

1467
02:11:50,749 --> 02:11:51,909
what I seen?

1468
02:11:52,017 --> 02:11:53,484
 Number one,

1469
02:11:53,586 --> 02:11:55,918
shut this door,
It's freezin',

1470
02:11:55,988 --> 02:11:58,980
Number two, shut that door,
It's freezin',

1471
02:11:59,091 --> 02:12:01,491
layin' on my back,
my fingers poked in my ears,

1472
02:12:01,594 --> 02:12:04,427
tryin' to shut out
who's got a bag of diamonds,

1473
02:12:04,496 --> 02:12:06,691
who's carrying a tray...

1474
02:12:06,765 --> 02:12:09,063
If you wanna get three feet up a bull's ass,

1475
02:12:09,134 --> 02:12:12,729
just listen to what sweethearts
whisper to one another,

1476
02:12:12,805 --> 02:12:18,505
In fact, if y'all gonna wimble-wimble
all night, I'm gonna sleep in with him,

1477
02:12:33,225 --> 02:12:36,490
- I'll say good night,
- No,

1478
02:12:39,565 --> 02:12:41,556
Please...

1479
02:12:42,568 --> 02:12:44,331
don't say good night,

1480
02:13:08,961 --> 02:13:12,658
wars make some things pointless,

1481
02:13:15,868 --> 02:13:19,201
It's hard to imagine a wedding,

1482
02:13:20,739 --> 02:13:24,038
I think even my father
would recognize that,

1483
02:13:24,610 --> 02:13:27,044
Ada, I wanna marry you,

1484
02:13:28,347 --> 02:13:29,871
If you'll have me,

1485
02:13:31,483 --> 02:13:36,420
Isn't there some religion where you just
have to say I marry you three times,

1486
02:13:36,488 --> 02:13:38,456
and you're man and wife?

1487
02:13:39,391 --> 02:13:41,359
I marry you,

1488
02:13:42,661 --> 02:13:44,788
I marry you, I marry you,

1489
02:13:49,868 --> 02:13:51,893
why is that funny?

1490
02:13:51,970 --> 02:13:57,772
I think it's I divorce you three times
and you're not married anymore,

1491
02:13:58,610 --> 02:14:00,544
I can wait for you,

1492
02:14:00,612 --> 02:14:06,073
Oh, Inman,
I marry you, I marry you, I marry you,

1493
02:14:06,185 --> 02:14:08,153
I marry you, I marry you,

1494
02:14:16,128 --> 02:14:19,825
I have so...
I have so many buttons, Sorry,

1495
02:14:23,469 --> 02:14:26,267
will you turn your back?

1496
02:14:37,483 --> 02:14:38,848
No,

1497
02:14:41,153 --> 02:14:42,620
No, I will not,

1500
02:16:28,594 --> 02:16:31,529
I'll lead the horse
at a pace your daddy can tolerate,

1501
02:16:31,597 --> 02:16:35,328
- You two go ahead now,
- No, I don't wanna do that,

1502
02:16:35,400 --> 02:16:38,096
- No, we can all go together,
- It's safer this way,

1503
02:16:38,170 --> 02:16:40,661
we're deserters,
No one has a quarrel with you,

1504
02:16:40,739 --> 02:16:42,730
He's right,

1505
02:16:42,808 --> 02:16:47,006
I gather I...
I need permission from you, Ruby,

1506
02:16:47,079 --> 02:16:50,207
if I reckon on livin' at Black Cove,

1507
02:16:59,591 --> 02:17:00,990
All right, then,

1509
02:17:04,930 --> 02:17:07,125
You stay on that horse,

1510
02:17:07,199 --> 02:17:10,134
And don't lose it,
Or sell it,

1511
02:17:11,003 --> 02:17:13,904
Gonna need it back on the farm,

1513
02:17:16,775 --> 02:17:18,766
All right, Daddy,

1514
02:17:22,948 --> 02:17:24,711
I don't wanna let you go,

1515
02:17:28,487 --> 02:17:31,684
I'll be with you by nightfall,

1516
02:17:36,528 --> 02:17:37,995
Ugh,

1517
02:17:39,798 --> 02:17:42,164
All right, then,

1518
02:18:12,798 --> 02:18:16,632
Hope that Georgia boy's
been tendin' to the animals,

1519
02:18:16,702 --> 02:18:19,637
- I knew you were thinkin' on him,
- I was not!

1520
02:18:19,705 --> 02:18:22,037
- I was thinkin' on swollen udders,
- Oh...!

1521
02:18:22,107 --> 02:18:26,339
- And before you say same difference...
- I'm sayin' nothin'!

1522
02:18:26,411 --> 02:18:30,905
Miss lovey-Dovey!
Miss lovey-Dovey!

1523
02:18:30,983 --> 02:18:33,008
Hey!

1524
02:18:33,118 --> 02:18:37,282
- That was a long funeral for your daddy,
- That was a wake,

1525
02:18:37,389 --> 02:18:38,947
That was Irish,

1526
02:18:40,926 --> 02:18:42,917
Now, your friend Georgia here...

1527
02:18:42,995 --> 02:18:46,692
we went down to visit you when
we heard you were harborin' deserters,

1528
02:18:46,765 --> 02:18:50,895
and he told us - after some persuasion -
you were up here,

1529
02:18:50,969 --> 02:18:53,836
we were up and down
this mountain,

1530
02:18:53,905 --> 02:18:55,236
Up and down,

1531
02:18:55,841 --> 02:18:57,672
There will be a reckoning,

1532
02:18:57,743 --> 02:19:00,678
when this war is over,
there will be a reckoning,

1533
02:19:02,347 --> 02:19:04,542
Did you make this coat?

1534
02:19:04,616 --> 02:19:06,607
Helpin' a deserter - that's treason,

1535
02:19:06,718 --> 02:19:11,212
Now, I know
it's half horse and half reverend,

1536
02:19:12,858 --> 02:19:14,826
A reckonin'?

1537
02:19:16,461 --> 02:19:19,589
The reckoning's for your world,

1538
02:19:19,998 --> 02:19:22,660
- It's not mine,

1539
02:19:26,471 --> 02:19:29,463
I'I be damned,
He's a hard bastard to kill,

1541
02:19:33,378 --> 02:19:35,744
-  No!
- Ruby!

1543
02:19:41,186 --> 02:19:42,710
 Inman!

1544
02:19:56,435 --> 02:19:58,266
- 
- Captain Teague!

1547
02:20:40,378 --> 02:20:44,405
- Come down from there!
- No, sir, Here is fine,

1548
02:20:44,483 --> 02:20:47,475
I'll just shoot the horse out from under you,

1549
02:20:47,552 --> 02:20:50,715
- You ridin' Captain Teague's animal?
- I am,

1550
02:20:50,822 --> 02:20:53,985
- He dead?
- I hope so,

1551
02:20:54,059 --> 02:20:58,428
look, give me your gun and ride on home,
I'm done fightin', I'm sick of it!

1552
02:20:58,497 --> 02:21:00,988
I give you my gun,
you're gonna shoot me dead,

1553
02:21:01,066 --> 02:21:02,226
I will not shoot you,

1554
02:21:02,300 --> 02:21:05,895
but nor am I goin' down this mountain
lookin' over my shoulder for you,

1555
02:21:05,971 --> 02:21:08,166
That's what they call a conundrum,

1556
02:21:12,577 --> 02:21:16,673
- I'll tell you what I got on my side,
- what you got on your side?

1557
02:21:23,522 --> 02:21:25,353
The confidence of youth,

1558
02:21:40,739 --> 02:21:42,900
Inman!

1559
02:21:59,891 --> 02:22:01,791

1562
02:22:34,226 --> 02:22:36,194
No!

1563
02:23:11,963 --> 02:23:13,191
I...

1564
02:23:14,065 --> 02:23:16,499
came... back,

1565
02:23:25,477 --> 02:23:27,843
I love you,

1567
02:24:00,979 --> 02:24:02,970
Baby,

1568
02:24:28,974 --> 02:24:32,432
what we have lost
will never be returned to us.

1569
02:24:33,979 --> 02:24:36,311
The land will not heal.

1570
02:24:37,148 --> 02:24:40,208
Too much blood.

1571
02:24:40,318 --> 02:24:43,879
The heart will not heal.

1572
02:24:43,989 --> 02:24:47,789
All we can do is make peace with the past

1573
02:24:47,859 --> 02:24:49,884
and try to learn from it.

1574
02:24:53,198 --> 02:24:57,760
- what are you doing?
- He died in the night, love,

1575
02:24:59,037 --> 02:25:00,971
Bring him here,

1576
02:25:01,039 --> 02:25:04,167
- Don't kill him,
- I'm not gonna kill him,

1577
02:25:04,242 --> 02:25:08,338
we have to try somethin'
or else he's gonna die too,

1578
02:25:08,413 --> 02:25:11,280
- It's all right,

1579
02:25:11,950 --> 02:25:14,441
we're gonna try a little trick,

1580
02:25:14,552 --> 02:25:17,020
- Shh,

1583
02:25:36,775 --> 02:25:41,940
There are days now
when I manage not to think of you.

1584
02:25:42,380 --> 02:25:47,374
when the needs of the farm
call with more urgency than my heart.

1585
02:25:48,820 --> 02:25:52,813
This time of year
there's so much life everywhere.

1586
02:25:54,826 --> 02:25:56,794
I find you in all of it.

1587
02:25:58,863 --> 02:26:01,855
As if you were still walking home to me.

1588
02:26:04,769 --> 02:26:09,001
If you could see us now
this Easter day at Black Cove,

1589
02:26:09,074 --> 02:26:12,566
you would know
every step of your journey was worth it.

1590
02:26:29,928 --> 02:26:33,364
Grace Inman, nobody said Eat,

1592
02:26:46,144 --> 02:26:50,877
For good friends, good food, good family,

1593
02:26:50,949 --> 02:26:54,077
all our blessings, O lord, we thank thee,

1594
02:26:54,185 --> 02:26:55,550
- Amen,
- Amen,

1595
02:26:55,620 --> 02:26:57,247
- Amen,
- Amen,

1596
02:26:57,355 --> 02:26:59,880
-  Amen!

1597
02:26:59,991 --> 02:27:03,688
- Sweetheart, there's no cider,
-  That's for you,

1598
02:27:03,761 --> 02:27:07,993
Right, I'd best...
I'd best fetch it, I got my orders,

1599
02:27:11,102 --> 02:27:15,004
I looked once more down Sally's well,

1600
02:27:15,073 --> 02:27:19,134
and this time
there was nothin' there to haunt me.

1601
02:27:20,145 --> 02:27:22,079
Just clouds.

1602
02:27:22,147 --> 02:27:26,447
Clouds, and then... sun.

1603
02:31:10,174 --> 02:31:16,374
Just to lose him again?

1604
02:31:58,022 --> 02:32:03,858
Through musket fire

1605
02:32:33,691 --> 02:32:39,527
through death 's dark veil

